1031 void US_ConvertGui::reset( void )
1032 {
1033  lw_triple ->clear();
1034

1233 
1234  if ( allData.size() > 0 )

1236  int status = QMessageBox::information( this,
1237  tr( "New Data Warning" ),
1238  tr( "This will erase all data currently on the screen, and "
1239  "reset the program to its starting condition. No hard-drive "
1240  "data or database information will be affected. Proceed? " ),
1241  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
1242  0, 0, 1 );
1243

1245  }
1246 
1247  reset();
1248

1252  reference_end = 0;

2100 // Import sub-directory contains MWL data
2101 void US_ConvertGui::importMWL( void )
2102 {

2104  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
2105 
2106  // Read the data

2113  { // If import problem was duplicate wavelengths, report it.
2114  QMessageBox::warning( this,
2115  tr( "Duplicate Wavelengths" ),
2116  tr( "Duplicate wavelengths were encountered in the import"
2117  " of the Multi-WaveLength data.\n\n"

2126  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();

2128  qApp->processEvents();

2131

2133  isMwl = true;
2134  runType = "RI";
2135  mwl_data.run_values( runID, runType );
2136 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iM: runID runType" << runID << runType;

2140 // if ( oldRunType != runType ) ExpData.clear();

2150  ct_tolerance->setValue( scanTolerance );
2151  connectTolerance( true );

2154  show_mwl_control( true );
2155 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iM: RTN:show_mwl_control";
2156  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
2157 
2158  // Set initial lambda range; build the output data
2159  le_status->setText( tr( "Duplicating wavelengths ..." ) );
2160  qApp->processEvents();
2161  slambda = mwl_data.countOf( "slambda" );
2162  elambda = mwl_data.countOf( "elambda" );
2163 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iM: set_lambd sl el" << slambda << elambda;

2184  QDir::Files, QDir::Name );

2187  if ( tmst_dname.right( 1 ) != "/" )
2188  tmst_dname += "/";
2189

2191  { // Looks like we have a TMST and corresponding Defs XML
2192  tmst_fnamei = tmsfs[ 0 ];
2193  defs_fnamei = tmsfs[ 1 ];
2194 
2195  if ( tmst_fnamei.contains( ".tmst" ) &&
2196  defs_fnamei.contains( ".xml" ) )
2197  { // Have both files, so save full path to TMST
2198  tmst_fnamei = tmst_dname + tmst_fnamei;
2199  }
2200 
2201  else if ( tmsfs[ 0 ].contains( ".xml" ) &&
2202  tmsfs[ 1 ].contains( ".tmst" ) )
2203  { // Have both files (in opposite order), so save full path to TMST
2204  tmst_fnamei = tmst_dname + tmsfs[ 1 ];
2205  }
2206

2209  tmst_fnamei.clear();
2210  }
2211  }

2214  {
2215  tmst_fnamei.clear();
2216  }
2217

2219  qApp->processEvents();

2221 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iM: DONE";

2227 // Import simulation data in AUC form
2228 void US_ConvertGui::importAUC( void )
2229 {
2230  QString importDir = currentDir;
2231  QDir readDir( importDir );
2232 
2233 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iA: CURRENT DIR_1: " << importDir;
2234 
2235  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
2236  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading AUC data ..." ) );
2237  QStringList nameFilters = QStringList( "*.auc" );
2238  QStringList files = readDir.entryList( nameFilters,
2239  QDir::Files | QDir::Readable, QDir::Name );
2240  allData .clear();
2241  all_tripinfo.clear();
2242 
2243  // *** Determine 1st runType to process *************//
2244  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
2245  {
2246  QMap<QString, int>::iterator jj;
2247  for ( jj = runTypes_map.begin(); jj != runTypes_map.end(); ++jj )
2248  {
2249  if ( jj.value() )
2250  {
2251  type_to_process = jj.key();
2252  break;
2253  }
2254  }
2255  }
2256 
2257 
2258 
2259  qDebug() << "DEBUG for HEXAL: type_to_process: " << type_to_process;
2260  //*****************************************************//
2261 
2262  //Read AProfile here: IMPORTANT -- read only channels corresponding to current runType:
2263  read_aprofile_data_from_aprofile();
2264 
2265 
2266  for ( int trx = 0; trx < files.size(); trx++ )
2267  {
2268  QString fname = files[ trx ];
2269  QString fpath = importDir + fname;
2270 
2271  //*** ALEXEY: in case of combined runs, start with the 1st OS (ITF) ****//
2272  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
2273  {
2274  QString typerun = QString( fname ).section( ".", -5, -5 );
2275 
2276  if ( typerun != type_to_process )
2277  continue;
2278  }
2279 
2280  //********************************************************************//
2281 
2282  US_DataIO::RawData rdata;
2283  US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo;
2284 
2285  // Get a raw data from an auc file
2286  US_DataIO::readRawData( fpath, rdata );
2287 
2288  // Give it a new unique GUID, since we are making a copy
2289  QString uuidst = US_Util::new_guid();
2290  US_Util::uuid_parse( uuidst, (unsigned char*)&rdata.rawGUID );
2291  DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iA: trx" << trx << "uuid" << uuidst << importDir;
2292 
2293  //Correct/parse channels' description:
2294  if ( !us_convert_auto_mode )
2295  {
2296  qDebug() << "Description before: " << rdata.description;
2297  correct_description( rdata.description, QString::number( rdata.cell ), QString( rdata.channel ) );
2298  qDebug() << "Description after: " << rdata.description;
2299  }
2300 
2301  // Save the raw data for this triple
2302  allData << rdata;
2303 
2304  // Save triple information
2305  QString triple = QString::number( rdata.cell ) + " / "
2306  + QString( rdata.channel ) + " / "
2307  + QString::number( qRound( rdata.scanData[ 0 ].wavelength ) );
2308  tripinfo.tripleID = trx + 1;
2309  tripinfo.tripleDesc = triple;
2310  tripinfo.description = rdata.description;
2311  tripinfo.channelID = trx + 1;
2312  tripinfo.excluded = false;
2313 
2314  // if ( us_convert_auto_mode )
2315  // {
2316  // if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
2317  // {
2318  // all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
2319  // }
2320  // else
2321  // all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
2322  // }
2323  // else
2324  // all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
2325 
2326  all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
2327  }
2328 
2329  // *** set key/value in the type_map for processed type to 0 && reset type_to_process ****//
2330  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
2331  runTypes_map[ type_to_process ] = 0;
2332 
2333  qApp->processEvents();
2334  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
2335 
2336  QString fname = files[ 0 ];
2337  runType = QString( fname ).section( ".", -5, -5 );
2338  runID = QString( fname ).section( ".", 0, -6 );
2339 
2340  //For DataFromDisk, we need to append runID with something like "-dataDiskRun-{autoflowID_passed}"
2341  if ( dataSource.contains("Disk") && us_convert_auto_mode && !us_import_ssf_abde )
2342  runID += QString("-dataDiskRun-") + QString::number( autoflowID_passed );
2343 
2344  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
2345  {
2346  runID += QString("-") + QString( type_to_process );
2347 
2348  runTypeList << runID;
2349 
2350  //ALEXEY: <- bug fixed
2351  runType = type_to_process;
2352  }
2353 
2354  // //TEMP
2355  //runID += QString("-test");
2356 
2357 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iA: RUNID from files[0]: files[0]" << fname << ", runID: " << runID;
2358 
2359 
2360  le_runID2->setText( runID );
2361  runID = le_runID2->text();
2362  le_runID ->setText( runID );
2363  scanTolerance = 5.0;
2364 
2365 
2366  if ( ! init_output_data() ) //Copy of allData -> outData
2367  return;
2368 
2369  setTripleInfo();
2370 
2371  //DESC SET 1
2372  // if ( !us_convert_auto_mode )
2373  // le_description -> setText( correct_description( allData[ 0 ].description ) );
2374  // else
2375  le_description -> setText( allData[ 0 ].description );
2376 
2377  init_excludes();
2378  plot_current();
2379  saveStatus = NOT_SAVED;
2380  enableControls();
2381 
2382  // Point to any existing time state file
2383  QDir ddir( currentDir );
2384 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:iA: CURRENT DIR_2: " << currentDir;
2385  QStringList tmsfs = ddir.entryList( QStringList( "*.time_state.*" ),
2386  QDir::Files, QDir::Name );
2387  QString defs_fnamei;
2388  QString tmst_dname = currentDir;
2389  if ( tmst_dname.right( 1 ) != "/" )
2390  tmst_dname += "/";
2391 DbgLv(1) << "rTS: tmst_dname" << tmst_dname << "tmsfs count" << tmsfs.count();
2392 
2393  if ( tmsfs.count() == 2 )
2394  { // Looks like we have a TMST and corresponding Defs XML
2395  tmst_fnamei = tmsfs[ 0 ];
2396  defs_fnamei = tmsfs[ 1 ];
2397 DbgLv(1) << "rTS: tmsfs" << tmst_fnamei << defs_fnamei;
2398 
2399  if ( tmst_fnamei.contains( ".tmst" ) &&
2400  defs_fnamei.contains( ".xml" ) )
2401  { // Have both files, so save full path to TMST
2402  tmst_fnamei = tmst_dname + tmst_fnamei;
2403  }
2404 
2405  else if ( tmsfs[ 0 ].contains( ".xml" ) &&
2406  tmsfs[ 1 ].contains( ".tmst" ) )
2407  { // Have both files (in opposite order), so save full path to TMST
2408  tmst_fnamei = tmst_dname + tmsfs[ 1 ];
2409  }
2410 
2411  else
2412  { // Do not have both files, so clear TMST file path
2413  tmst_fnamei.clear();
2414  }
2415 DbgLv(1) << "rTS: tmst,defs fnamei" << tmst_fnamei << defs_fnamei;
2416  }
2417 
2418  else // If file does not exist, clear name
2419  {
2420 DbgLv(1) << "rTS: NON_EXIST:" << tmst_fnamei;
2421  tmst_fnamei.clear();
2422  }
2423 
2424  if ( !us_convert_auto_mode )
2425  {
2426  //le_status->setText( tr( "AUC data import IS COMPLETE." ) );
2427  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading Data from Disk Successful." ) );
2428  }
2429 
2430  pb_showTmst->setEnabled( ! tmst_fnamei.isEmpty() );
2431 
2432  // check number scans
2433  check_scans();
2434 }

2437 //Correct description for double solution names
2438 QString US_ConvertGui::correct_description( QString & description, QString cell, QString chan )
2439 {
2440  QString desc_corrected;
2441  if ( description.contains(";") && description.contains("A:") && description.contains("B:") )
2442  {
2443  //Format: "Cell 1: A: solname, comment; B: solname, comment"
2444  QStringList desc_all = description.split(";");
2445  QString desc_A = desc_all[0];
2446  QString desc_B = desc_all[ desc_all.size()-1 ];
2447  QStringList desc_from_allData_A = desc_A.split(":");
2448  QStringList desc_from_allData_B = desc_B.split(":");
2449 
2450  // QString desc_chan_A = desc_from_allData_A[2].simplified().split(",")[0];
2451  // QString desc_chan_B = desc_from_allData_B[1].simplified().split(" ")[0];
2452  // QString desc_corrected = desc_from_allData_A[0] + ":" +
2453  // desc_from_allData_A[1] + ": " +
2454  // desc_chan_A + ";" +
2455  // desc_from_allData_B[0] + ": " +
2456  // desc_chan_B;
2457 
2458  //QString desc_chan_A = desc_from_allData_A[2].simplified();
2459  //QString desc_chan_B = desc_from_allData_B[1].simplified();
2460 
2461  QString desc_chan_A = desc_from_allData_A[ desc_from_allData_A.size() - 1 ].simplified();
2462  QString desc_chan_B = desc_from_allData_B[ desc_from_allData_B.size() - 1 ].simplified();
2463  desc_corrected = desc_chan_A + " -- " + desc_chan_B;
2464 
2465  qDebug() << "DESC A: " << desc_chan_A;
2466  qDebug() << "DESC B: " << desc_chan_B;
2467  qDebug() << "DESC CORR: " << desc_corrected;
2468 
2469  if ( chan == "A" )
2470  description = desc_chan_A;
2471  if ( chan == "B" )
2472  description = desc_chan_B;
2473  }
2474 
2475  return desc_corrected;
2476 }
2477 
2478 void US_ConvertGui::check_scans()
2479 {
2480  int nsmin = 99999;
2481  for (int ii = 0; ii < allData.size(); ii++ ) {
2482  nsmin = qMin(allData[ii].scanCount(), nsmin);
2483  }
2484 
2485  QStringList ccws_list;
2486  bool same = true;
2487  for (int ii = 0; ii < allData.size(); ii++ ) {
2488  int ns = allData[ii].scanCount();
2489  // In most cases, df is zero. However, occasionally it becomes 1,
2490  // and the following code removes it from end of the code.
2491  int df = ns - nsmin;
2492  int cell = allData[ii].cell;
2493  char channel = allData[ii].channel;
2494  double lambda = allData[ii].scanData.first().wavelength;
2495  ccws_list << tr("%1 / %2 / %3 : number of scans = %4").arg(cell).arg(channel).arg(lambda).arg(ns);
2496  if ( df > 0 ) {
2497  same = false;
2498  allData[ii].scanData.remove( ns - df, df );
2499  }
2500  }
2501  if ( ! same ) {
2502  US_WidgetsDialog *error_wgt = new US_WidgetsDialog(this);
2503  error_wgt->setWindowTitle("Warning !!!");
2504  error_wgt->setPalette(US_GuiSettings::frameColor());
2505  QPlainTextEdit *msg = new QPlainTextEdit();
2506  msg->setStyleSheet("QPlainTextEdit { background-color: white; }");
2507  msg->setReadOnly(true);
2508  msg->appendPlainText("Please note:\nThe number of scans per triple differs for some triples:\n");
2509  foreach (QString line, ccws_list) {
2510  msg->appendPlainText(line);
2511  }
2512  msg->appendPlainText(tr( "\nAmong other reasons, this can occur when the run has been "
2513  "aborted in the middle of data acquisition. The number of scans "
2514  "for all triples has been set to %1, triples with additional "
2515  "scans will be truncated to %1 scans.").arg(nsmin));
2516  QPushButton *pb_ok = us_pushbutton("&OK");
2517  pb_ok->setIcon(this->style()->standardIcon(QStyle::SP_DialogOkButton));
2518  QGridLayout* lyt = new QGridLayout();
2519  lyt->addWidget(msg, 0, 0, 5, 5);
2520  lyt->addWidget(pb_ok, 5, 2, 1, 1);
2521  lyt->setMargin(2);
2522  error_wgt->setLayout(lyt);
2523  error_wgt->setMinimumSize(500, 500);
2524  connect(pb_ok, &QPushButton::clicked, error_wgt, &US_WidgetsDialog::accept);
2525  error_wgt->exec();
2526  }
2527 }

2529 // Enable the common dialog controls when there is data
2530 void US_ConvertGui::enableControls( void )
2531 {
2532  if ( allData.size() == 0 )
2533  reset();
2534 
2535  else
2536  {
2537 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: enabCtl: have-data" << allData.size() << all_tripinfo.size();
2538  // Ok to enable some buttons now
2539  pb_showTmst ->setEnabled( ! tmst_fnamei.isEmpty() );
2540  pb_details ->setEnabled( true );
2541  pb_solution ->setEnabled( true );
2542  cb_centerpiece ->setEnabled( true );
2543  pb_editRuninfo ->setEnabled( true );
2544 
2545  // Ok to drop scan if not the only one
2546  int currentScanCount = 0;
2547 
2548  for ( int i = 0; i < all_tripinfo.size(); i++ )
2549  if ( ! all_tripinfo[ i ].excluded ) currentScanCount++;
2550 
2551  bool drops = ( currentScanCount > 1 );
2552  pb_dropTrips ->setEnabled( drops );
2553  pb_dropCelch ->setEnabled( drops && isMwl );
2554  pb_dropChan ->setEnabled( drops && isMwl );
2555 
2556  if ( runType == "RI" )
2557  pb_reference->setEnabled( ! referenceDefined );
2558 
2559  if ( us_convert_auto_mode && type_to_process == "RI" )
2560  pb_reference->setEnabled( ! referenceDefined );
2561 
2562 
2563  if ( subsets.size() < 1 )
2564  {
2565  // Allow user to define subsets, if he hasn't already
2566  pb_define ->setEnabled( true );
2567  }
2568 
2569  // Disable load buttons if there is data
2570  pb_import ->setEnabled( false );
2571  pb_loadUS3->setEnabled( false );
2572 
2573  // Most triples are ccw
2574  lb_triple ->setText( tr( "Cell / Channel / Wavelength" ) );
2575  connectTolerance( false );
2576  ct_tolerance->setNumButtons ( 2 );
2577  ct_tolerance->setRange ( 0.0, 100.0 );
2578  ct_tolerance->setSingleStep ( 1.0 );
2579  ct_tolerance->setValue ( scanTolerance );
2580 
2581  // Default tolerances are different for wavelength data
2582  if ( runType == "WA" )
2583  {
2584  // First of all, wavelength triples are ccr.
2585  lb_triple ->setText( tr( "Cell / Channel / Radius" ) );
2586  ct_tolerance->setNumButtons ( 3 );
2587  ct_tolerance->setRange ( 0.0, 10.0 );
2588  ct_tolerance->setSingleStep ( 0.001 );
2589  ct_tolerance->setValue ( scanTolerance );
2590  }
2591 
2592  connectTolerance( true );
2593 
2594  // Let's calculate if we're eligible to copy this triple info to all
2595  // or to save it
2596  // We have to check against GUID's, because solutions won't have
2597  // solutionID's yet if they are created as needed offline
2598  QRegExp rx( "^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$" );
2599 
2600  pb_applyAll -> setEnabled( false );
2601 // if ( all_tripinfo.size() > 1 &&
2602 // rx.exactMatch( all_tripinfo[ tripListx ].solution.solutionGUID ) )
2603  if ( out_chaninfo.size() > 1 &&
2604  rx.exactMatch( out_chaninfo[ tripListx ].solution.solutionGUID ) )
2605  {
2606  pb_applyAll -> setEnabled( true );
2607  }
2608 
2609  enableRunIDControl( saveStatus == NOT_SAVED );
2610 
2611  enableSaveBtn();
2612 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: enabCtl: enabSvBtn complete";
2613  }
2614 }

2670 // Enable the "save" button, if appropriate
2671 // Let's use the same logic to populate the todo list too
2672 void US_ConvertGui::enableSaveBtn( void )
2673 {
2674  lw_todoinfo->clear();
2675  int count = 0;
2676  bool completed = true;
2677 DbgLv(1) << " enabCtl: tLx infsz" << tripListx << out_chaninfo.count();
2678  cb_centerpiece->setLogicalIndex( out_chaninfo[ tripListx ].centerpiece );
2679 
2680  if ( allData.size() == 0 )
2681  {
2682  count++;
2683  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count )
2684  + tr( ": Load or import some AUC data" ) );
2685  completed = false;
2686  }
2687 
2688  // Do we have any triples?
2689  if ( all_tripinfo.size() == 0 )
2690  {
2691  count++;
2692  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count )
2693  + tr( ": Load or import some AUC data" ) );
2694  completed = false;
2695  }
2696 
2697  // Is the run info defined?
2698  QRegExp rx( "^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$" );
2699 
2700  // Not checking operator on disk -- defined as "Local"
2701  if ( ( ExpData.rotorID == 0 ) ||
2702  ( ExpData.calibrationID == 0 ) ||
2703  ( ExpData.labID == 0 ) ||
2704  ( ExpData.instrumentID == 0 ) ||
2705  ( ExpData.label.isEmpty() ) ||
2706  ( ! rx.exactMatch( ExpData.project.projectGUID ) ) )
2707  {
2708  if ( ! referenceDefined )
2709  {
2710  count++;
2711  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count )
2712  + tr( ": Modify run ID (optional)" ) );
2713  }
2714  count++;
2715  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count )
2716  + tr( ": Edit run information" ) );
2717  completed = false;
2718  }
2719 
2720  // Have we filled out all the c/c/w info?
2721  // Check GUIDs, because solutionID's may not be present yet.
2722  foreach ( US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo, out_chaninfo )
2723  {
2724  if ( ! rx.exactMatch( tripinfo.solution.solutionGUID ) )
2725  {
2726  count++;
2727  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count ) +
2728  tr( ": Select solution for triple " ) +
2729  tripinfo.tripleDesc );
2730  completed = false;
2731  }
2732  }
2733 
2734  foreach ( US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo, out_chaninfo )
2735  {
2736  if ( tripinfo.centerpiece == 0 )
2737  {
2738  count++;
2739  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count ) +
2740  tr( ": Select centerpiece for triple " ) +
2741  tripinfo.tripleDesc );
2742  completed = false;
2743  }
2744  }
2745 
2746  if ( disk_controls->db() )
2747  {
2748  // Verify connectivity
2749  US_Passwd pw;
2750  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
2751  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
2752 
2753  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
2754  {
2755  count++;
2756  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count ) +
2757  tr( ": Verify database connectivity" ) );
2758  completed = false;
2759  }
2760 
2761  // Information is there, but we need to see if the runID exists in the
2762  // DB. If we didn't load it from there, then we shouldn't be able to sync
2763  int recStatus = ExpData.checkRunID( &db );
2764 
2765  // if a record is found but saveStatus==BOTH,
2766  // then we are editing that record
2767  if ( ( recStatus == US_DB2::OK ) && ( saveStatus != BOTH ) ) // ||
2768  // ( ! ExpData.syncOK ) )
2769  {
2770  count++;
2771  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count ) +
2772  tr( ": Select a different runID" ) );
2773  completed = false;
2774  }
2775 
2776  // Not checking operator on disk -- defined as "Local"
2777  if ( ExpData.operatorID == 0 )
2778  {
2779  count++;
2780  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count )
2781  + tr( ": Select operator in run information" ) );
2782  completed = false;
2783  }
2784 
2785  }
2786 
2787  // This can go on the todo list, but should not prevent user from saving
2788  if ( ( runType == "RI" ) && ( ! referenceDefined ) )
2789  {
2790  count++;
2791  lw_todoinfo->addItem( QString::number( count ) +
2792  tr( ": Define reference scans" ) );
2793 
2794  if ( count == 1 )
2795  pb_reference->setEnabled( true );
2796  }
2797 
2798  // If we made it here, user can save
2799  pb_saveUS3 ->setEnabled( completed );
2800 }

3718 //get index of ProtInfo's Solutions based on channel name && data type:
3719 int US_ConvertGui::getProtSolIndex( QString channel_name, QString dtype )
3720 {
3721  int index = 0;
3722  channel_name.simplified();
3723  channel_name.replace( " ", "" );
3724 
3725  QStringList channelList = channel_name.split("/");
3726  QString channel_name_mod = channelList[0] + " / " + channelList[1];
3727 
3728  qDebug() << "In getProtSolIndex(): channel_name_mod -- " << channel_name_mod;
3729 
3730  for ( int i=0; i < ProtInfo.ProtSolutions.chsols.size(); ++i )
3731  {
3732  qDebug() << "ProtInfo.ProtSolutions.chsols[ i ].channel -- " << ProtInfo.ProtSolutions.chsols[ i ].channel;
3733  if ( ProtInfo.ProtSolutions.chsols[ i ].channel. startsWith( channel_name_mod ) )
3734  {
3735  index = i;
3736  break;
3737  }
3738  }
3739 
3740  return index;
3741 }
3742 
3743 //Check for consistency btw channel's name, dataType, && optics system
3744 bool US_ConvertGui::isCorrectDataType( QString channel_name, QString dtype )
3745 {
3746  bool isConsistent = true;
3747  QString data_type_from_optics;
3748 
3749  for ( int i=0; i < ProtInfo.ProtOptics.chopts.size(); ++i )
3750  {
3751  if ( ProtInfo.ProtOptics.chopts[ i ].channel == channel_name )
3752  {
3753  data_type_from_optics = ProtInfo.ProtOptics.chopts[ i ].data_type;
3754  break;
3755  }
3756  }
3757 
3758  qDebug() << "In isCorrectDataType(): data_type_from_optics, dtype -- "
3759  << data_type_from_optics << ", " << dtype;
3760 
3761  if ( data_type_from_optics != dtype )
3762  isConsistent = false;
3763 
3764  return isConsistent;
3765 }

3807  return;

3810  return;

3841 // Load AUC data from a specified directory on local disk
3842 void US_ConvertGui::loadUS3Disk( QString dir )
3843 {
3844  resetAll();
3845  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading data from local disk ..." ) );
3846  qApp->processEvents();
3847 
3848  // Check the runID
3849  QStringList components = dir.split( "/", QString::SkipEmptyParts );
3850  QString new_runID = components.last();
3851 
3852  QRegExp rx( "^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,80}$" );
3853  if ( rx.indexIn( new_runID ) < 0 )
3854  {
3855  QMessageBox::warning( this,
3856  tr( "Bad runID Name" ),
3857  tr( "The runID name may consist only of alphanumeric\n"
3858  "characters, the underscore, and the hyphen." ) );
3859  return;
3860  }
3861 
3862  // Set the runID and directory
3863  runID = new_runID;
3864  le_runID ->setText( runID );
3865  le_runID2->setText( runID );
3866  le_dir ->setText( dir );
3867  currentDir = QString( dir );
3868 
3869  // Reload the AUC data
3870  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading data from Disk (raw data) ..." ) );
3871  qApp->processEvents();
3872 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: ldUS3Dk: call read";
3873  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
3874  int status = US_Convert::readUS3Disk( dir, allData, all_tripinfo, runType );
3875  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
3876 
3877  if ( status == US_Convert::NODATA )
3878  {
3879  QMessageBox::warning( this,
3880  tr( "No Files Found" ),
3881  tr( "There were no files of the form *.auc\n"
3882  "found in the specified directory." ) );
3883  return;
3884  }
3885 
3886  if ( status == US_Convert::NOAUC )
3887  {
3888  QMessageBox::warning( this,
3889  tr( "UltraScan Error" ),
3890  tr( "Could not read data file.\n" ) );
3891  return;
3892  }
3893 
3894  // Now try to read the xml file
3895 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: ldUS3Dk: call rdExp sz(trinfo)" << all_tripinfo.count();
3896  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading data from Disk (experiment) ..." ) );
3897  qApp->processEvents();
3898  ExpData.clear();
3899  status = ExpData.readFromDisk( all_tripinfo, runType, runID, dir );
3900 
3901  if ( status == US_Convert::CANTOPEN )
3902  {
3903  QString readFile = runID + "."
3904  + runType + ".xml";
3905  QMessageBox::information( this,
3906  tr( "Error" ),
3907  tr( "US3 run data ok, but unable to assocate run with DB.\n " ) +
3908  tr( "Cannot open read file: " ) + dir + readFile );
3909  }
3910 
3911  else if ( status == US_Convert::BADXML )
3912  {
3913  QString readFile = runID + "."
3914  + runType + ".xml";
3915  QMessageBox::information( this,
3916  tr( "Error" ),
3917  tr( "US3 run data ok, but there is an error in association with DB.\n"
3918  "Improper XML in read file: " ) + dir + readFile );
3919  }
3920 
3921  else if ( status != US_Convert::OK )
3922  {
3923  QMessageBox::information( this,
3924  tr( "Error" ),
3925  tr( "Unknown error: " ) + status );
3926  }
3927 
3928  // Now that we have the experiment, let's read the rest of the
3929  // solution and project information
3930  le_status->setText( tr( "Loading data from Disk (project) ..." ) );
3931  qApp->processEvents();
3932 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: ldUS3Dk: call prj-rDk";
3933  status = ExpData.project.readFromDisk( ExpData.project.projectGUID );
3934 
3935  // Error reporting
3936  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_PROJECT )
3937  {
3938  QMessageBox::information( this,
3939  tr( "Attention" ),
3940  tr( "The project was not found.\n"
3941  "Please select an existing project and try again.\n" ) );
3942  }
3943 
3944  else if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
3945  {
3946  QMessageBox::information( this,
3947  tr( "Disk Read Problem" ),
3948  tr( "Could not read data from the disk.\n"
3949  "Disk status: " ) + QString::number( status ) );
3950  }
3951 
3952  // and clear it out
3953  if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
3954  ExpData.project.clear();
3955 
3956  le_status->setText( tr( "Project and experiment are loaded." ) );
3957  qApp->processEvents();
3958  QString psolGUID = "";
3959 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: SOLCHK:loop";
3960 
3961  // Now the solutions
3962  for ( int ii = 0; ii < all_tripinfo.size(); ii++ )
3963  {
3964  QString csolGUID = all_tripinfo[ ii ].solution.solutionGUID;
3965 
3966  if ( csolGUID == psolGUID )
3967  {
3968  all_tripinfo[ ii ].solution = all_tripinfo[ ii - 1 ].solution;
3969  status = US_DB2::OK;
3970  continue;
3971  }
3972  else
3973  {
3974  if ( csolGUID.isEmpty() )
3975  {
3976 DbgLv(1) << "SOLCHK: ii csolGUID EMPTY" << ii << csolGUID;
3977  if ( ii > 0 )
3978  {
3979  csolGUID = psolGUID;
3980  all_tripinfo[ ii ].solution.solutionGUID = csolGUID;
3981  }
3982  }
3983  status = all_tripinfo[ ii ].solution.readFromDisk( csolGUID );
3984  psolGUID = csolGUID;
3985  }
3986 
3987  // Error reporting
3988  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_SOLUTION )
3989  {
3990  QMessageBox::information( this,
3991  tr( "Attention" ),

3994  "Please select an existing solution and try again.\n" ) );
3995 DbgLv(1) << "SOLERR: ii psolGUID csolGUI" << ii << psolGUID << csolGUID;
3996  }
3997 
3998  else if ( status == US_DB2::NO_BUFFER )
3999  {
4000  QMessageBox::information( this,
4001  tr( "Attention" ),
4002  tr( "The buffer this solution refers to was not found.\n"
4003  "Please restore and try again.\n" ) );
4004  }
4005 
4006  else if ( status == US_DB2::NO_ANALYTE )
4007  {
4008  QMessageBox::information( this,

4012  }
4013 
4014  else if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
4015  {
4016  QMessageBox::information( this,
4017  tr( "Disk Read Problem" ),
4018  tr( "Could not read data from the disk.\n"
4019  "Disk status: " ) + QString::number( status ) );
4020  }

4025  }
4026 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: SOLCHK:loop-END";
4027 
4028  le_status->setText( tr( "Solutions are now loaded." ) );
4029  qApp->processEvents();

4054  + "RIProfile.xml";
4055  QMessageBox::information( this,
4056  tr( "Error" ),

4058  tr( "Improper XML in read file: " ) + dir + readFile );

4287 void US_ConvertGui::getExpInfo_auto( void )
4288 {
4289 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: gExpInf: IN";
4290  ExpData.runID = le_runID -> text();
4291 
4342  // OK, proceed
4343 
4344  // Calculate average temperature
4345  double sum = 0.0;
4346  double count = 0.0;
4347  for ( int ii = 0; ii < allData.size(); ii++ )
4348  {
4349  US_DataIO::RawData* raw = &allData[ ii ];
4350  int kscan = raw->scanData.size();
4351  for ( int jj = 0; jj < kscan; jj++ )
4352  {
4353  sum += raw->scanData[ jj ].temperature;
4354  }
4355 
4356  count += kscan;
4357  }
4358 
4359  ExpData.runTemp = QString::number( sum / count );
4360 
4361  // Load information we're passing
4362  char* optSysPtr = ExpData.opticalSystem.data();
4363  strncpy( optSysPtr, allData[ 0 ].type, 2 );
4364  optSysPtr[ 2 ] = '\0';
4365 
4366  double ss_reso = 100.0;
4367  // If debug_text so directs, change set_speed_resolution
4368  QStringList dbgtxt = US_Settings::debug_text();
4369  for ( int ii = 0; ii < dbgtxt.count(); ii++ )
4370  { // If debug text modifies ss_reso, apply it
4371  if ( dbgtxt[ ii ].startsWith( "SetSpeedReso" ) )
4372  ss_reso = QString( dbgtxt[ ii ] ).section( "=", 1, 1 ).toDouble();
4373  }
4374 
4375  // A list of unique rpms
4376  ExpData.rpms.clear();
4377  for ( int ii = 0; ii < allData.size(); ii++ )
4378  {
4379  US_DataIO::RawData* raw = &allData[ ii ];
4380  for ( int jj = 0; jj < raw->scanData.size(); jj++ )
4381  {
4382  double rpm = raw->scanData[ jj ].rpm;
4383  rpm = qRound( rpm / ss_reso ) * ss_reso;
4384  if ( ! ExpData.rpms.contains( rpm ) )
4385  ExpData.rpms << rpm;
4386  }
4387  }
4388 
4389  // Now sort the rpm list. Use a modified bubble sort;
4390  // the list might already be almost ordered
4391  bool done = false;
4392  while ( !done )
4393  {
4394  done = true;
4395  for ( int i = 0; i < ExpData.rpms.size() - 1; i++ )
4396  {
4397  if ( ExpData.rpms[ i ] > ExpData.rpms[ i + 1 ] )
4398  {
4399  ExpData.rpms.swap( i, i + 1 );
4400  done = false;
4401  }
4402  }
4403  }
4404 
4405 
4406 // ALEXEY: fill the rest of ExpData from protocol saved, not from US_Exp..Gui...
4407 
4408 // int dbdisk = ( disk_controls->db() ) ? US_Disk_DB_Controls::DB

4722 void US_ConvertGui::changeDescription( void )

4967 void US_ConvertGui::checkTemperature( void )
4968 {
4969  // Temperature check
4970  double dt = 0.0;
4971 
4972  foreach( US_DataIO::RawData triple, allData )
4973  {
4974  double temp_spread = triple.temperature_spread();
4975  dt = ( temp_spread > dt ) ? temp_spread : dt;
4976  }
4977 
4978  if ( dt > US_Settings::tempTolerance() )
4979  {
4980  QMessageBox::warning( this,
4981  tr( "Temperature Problem" ),
4982  tr( "The temperature in this run varied over the course\n"
4983  "of the run to a larger extent than allowed by the\n"
4984  "current threshold (" )
4985  + QString::number( US_Settings::tempTolerance(), 'f', 1 )
4986  + " " + DEGC + tr( "). The accuracy of experimental\n"
4987  "results may be affected significantly." ) );
4988  }
4989 }

5082 // Function to exclude user-selected scans
5083 void US_ConvertGui::exclude_scans( void )
5084 {
5085  US_Convert::Excludes excludes = allExcludes[ tripDatax ];
5086 
5087  // Scans actually start at index 0
5088  int scanStart = (int)ct_from->value() - 1;
5089  int scanEnd = (int)ct_to ->value() - 1;
5090 
5091  // Sometimes the user leaves this at 0
5092  scanStart = ( scanStart < 0 ) ? 0 : scanStart;
5093  int scanCount = scanEnd - scanStart + 1;
5094 
5095  // Find the first scan to exclude, but account for the already excluded
5096  int scanNdx = 0;
5097  while ( scanNdx < scanStart )
5098  {
5099  if ( excludes.contains( scanNdx ) )
5100  scanStart++;
5101 
5102  scanNdx++;
5103  }
5104 
5105  // Now we have the starting point, so exclude some scans
5106  int excluded = 0;
5107  while ( excluded < scanCount )
5108  {
5109  if ( ! excludes.contains( scanNdx ) )
5110  {
5111  excluded++;
5112  allExcludes[ tripDatax ] << scanNdx;
5113  }
5114 
5115  scanNdx++;
5116  }
5117 
5118  enableScanControls();
5119 
5120  replot();
5121 }

5132 }

5148 
5149 void US_ConvertGui::process_subsets( void )
5150 {
5151  if ( subsets.size() < 1 )
5152  {
5153  // Not enough clicks to work with
5154  subsets.clear();
5155  pb_process ->setEnabled( true );
5156  return;
5157  }
5158 
5159  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
5160 
5161  // Add the top and bottom boundaries
5162  subsets << 5.7
5163  << 7.3;
5164 
5165  // Let's make sure the points are in sorted order
5166  for ( int i = 0; i < subsets.size() - 1; i++ )
5167  for ( int j = i + 1; j < subsets.size(); j++ )
5168  if ( subsets[ i ] > subsets[ j ] )
5169  {
5170  double temp = subsets[ i ];
5171  subsets[ i ] = subsets[ j ];
5172  subsets[ j ] = temp;
5173  }
5174 
5175  pb_process ->setEnabled( false );
5176  picker ->disconnect();
5177 
5178 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:pSS: split CALL";
5179  // Now let's split the triple
5180  US_Convert::splitRAData( allData, all_tripinfo, tripDatax, subsets );
5181 
5182  // We don't need this any more
5183  subsets.clear();
5184 
5185  // Reinitialize some things
5186  if ( ! init_output_data() )
5187  return;
5188  setTripleInfo();
5189  init_excludes();
5190  enableControls();
5191 
5192  plot_current();
5193  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5194 }

5264 // Plot all channel's last scans to pick the reference point
5265 void US_ConvertGui::plot_last_scans( double cent_point )
5266 {
5267  dataPlotClear( data_plot );
5268  grid = us_grid( data_plot );
5269  double maxR = -1.0e99;
5270  double minR = 1.0e99;
5271  double maxV = -1.0e99;
5272  double minV = 1.0e99;
5273  for (int ii = 0; ii < lw_triple->count(); ii++){
5274  int datax = out_chandatx[ ii ];
5275  US_DataIO::RawData* currentData = outData.at(datax);
5276  int nrpoints = currentData->pointCount();
5277  US_DataIO::Scan scan = currentData->scanData.last();
5278  DbgLv(1) << "Cell = " << currentData->cell << " , Channel = "
5279  << currentData->channel << " , Wavelenght = " << scan.wavelength;
5280  QVector< double > rvec( nrpoints );
5281  QVector< double > vvec( nrpoints );
5282  double* rr = rvec.data();
5283  double* vv = vvec.data();
5284  for ( int jj = 0; jj < nrpoints; jj++ )
5285  {
5286  rr[ jj ] = currentData->radius( jj );
5287  vv[ jj ] = scan.rvalues[ jj ];
5288  maxR = qMax( maxR, rr[ jj ] );
5289  minR = qMin( minR, rr[ jj ] );
5290  maxV = qMax( maxV, vv[ jj ] );
5291  minV = qMin( minV, vv[ jj ] );
5292  }
5293  QString title = tr( "Raw Data at %1 / %2 / %3" ).arg(currentData->cell).
5294  arg(currentData->channel).arg(scan.wavelength);
5295 
5296  QwtPlotCurve* curv = us_curve( data_plot, title );
5297  curv->setPen(QColor(Qt::yellow));
5298  curv->setSamples(rr, vv, nrpoints);
5299  }
5300 
5301  data_plot->setTitle( tr ("All Channels - First Wavelength - Last Scan"));
5302  double padR = ( maxR - minR ) / 30.0;
5303  double padV = ( maxV - minV ) / 30.0;
5304 
5305  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft , minV - padV, maxV + padV );
5306  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, minR - padR, maxR + padR );
5307 
5308  //Add v-line for 5.87 position as best guess (only first time!)
5309  if ( us_convert_auto_mode && first_time_plot_auto )
5310  {
5311  QwtPlotCurve* v_line_peak;
5312  double r[ 2 ];
5313  r[ 0 ] = cent_point;
5314  r[ 1 ] = cent_point;
5315 
5316 #if QT_VERSION < 0x050000
5317  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft );
5318 #else
5319  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = (QwtScaleDiv*)&(data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft ));
5320 #endif
5321 
5322  double padding = ( y_axis->upperBound() - y_axis->lowerBound() ) / 30.0;
5323 
5324  double v[ 2 ];
5325  v [ 0 ] = y_axis->upperBound() - padding;
5326  v [ 1 ] = y_axis->lowerBound() + padding;
5327 
5328  QString vline_name = "V-Position";
5329 
5330  v_line_peak = us_curve( data_plot, vline_name );
5331  v_line_peak ->setSamples( r, v, 2 );
5332 
5333  QPen pen = QPen( QBrush( Qt::red ), 2.0, Qt::DotLine );
5334  v_line_peak->setPen( pen );
5335  }

5700 // Reference calculation for pseudo-absorbance
5701 void US_ConvertGui::PseudoCalcAvg( void )
5702 {
5703  lw_triple->setEnabled( true );
5704  pb_lambnext->setEnabled( true );
5705  pb_lambprev->setEnabled( true );
5706  cb_lambplot->setEnabled( true );
5707  cb_lambstop->setEnabled( true );
5708  cb_lambstrt->setEnabled( true );
5709 
5710  if ( referenceDefined ) return; // Average calculation has already been done
5711 
5712  bool is_mwl_data = false;
5713  int temp_wvl = -1;
5714  for ( int ii = 0; ii < outData.size(); ii++) {
5715  int wvl = qRound(outData.at(ii)->scanData.first().wavelength);
5716  if ( temp_wvl == -1) {
5717  temp_wvl = wvl;
5718  continue;
5719  }
5720  if ( temp_wvl != wvl) {
5721  is_mwl_data = true;
5722  break;
5723  }
5724  }
5725 
5726  if ( is_mwl_data )
5727  { // Do calculations for each wavelength, if MWL
5728  PseudoCalcAvgMWL();
5729  return;
5730  }
5731 
5732  US_DataIO::RawData* referenceData = outData[ tripDatax ];
5733  int ref_size = referenceData->pointCount();
5734 
5735  for ( int ss = 0; ss < referenceData->scanCount(); ss++ )
5736  {
5737  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &referenceData->scanData[ ss ];
5738 
5739  int rr = 0;
5740  int count = 0;
5741  double sum = 0.0;
5742 
5743  while ( referenceData->radius( rr ) < reference_start &&
5744  rr < ref_size )
5745  rr++;
5746 
5747  while ( referenceData->radius( rr ) < reference_end &&
5748  rr < ref_size )
5749  {
5750  sum += scan->rvalues[ rr ];
5751  count++;
5752  rr++;
5753  }
5754 
5755  if ( count > 0 )
5756  {
5757  //ExpData.RIProfile << sum / count;
5758 
5759  if ( sum > 0 )
5760  ExpData.RIProfile << sum / count;
5761  else
5762  ExpData.RIProfile << 1.0;
5763  }
5764  else
5765  ExpData.RIProfile << 1.0; // See the log10 function, later
5766 
5767  }
5768 
5769  // Now average around excluded values
5770  int lastGood = 0;
5771  int countBad = 0;
5772  for ( int ss = 0; ss < ExpData.RIProfile.size(); ss++ )
5773  {
5774  // In case there are adjacent excluded scans...
5775  if ( allExcludes[ tripDatax ].contains( ss ) )
5776  countBad++;
5777 
5778  // Calculate average of before and after for intervening values
5779  else if ( countBad > 0 )
5780  {
5781  double newAvg = ( ExpData.RIProfile[ lastGood ]
5782  + ExpData.RIProfile[ ss ] ) / 2.0;
5783 
5784  for ( int rr = lastGood + 1; rr < ss; rr++ )
5785  ExpData.RIProfile[ rr ] = newAvg;
5786 
5787  countBad = 0;
5788  }
5789 
5790  // Normal situation -- value is not excluded
5791  else
5792  lastGood = ss;
5793 
5794  }
5795 
5796  // Now calculate the pseudo-absorbance
5797  int ndxmax = ExpData.RIProfile.size() - 1;
5798 
5799  // ATTENTION:
5800  // below, goes over data for all triples && applies ExpData.RIProfile calculated for the reference triple only
5801  // Ref. triple is (above): US_DataIO::RawData* referenceData = outData[ tripDatax ];
5802  // triplDatax -- index of the currently selected triple
5803  for ( int trx = 0; trx < outData.size(); trx++ )
5804  {
5805  US_DataIO::RawData* currentData = outData[ trx ];
5806  int kcpoint = currentData->pointCount();
5807 
5808  //HERE: calculate ExpData.RIProfile for each triple..
5809 
5810  for ( int ss = 0; ss < currentData->scanCount(); ss++ )
5811  {
5812  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &currentData->scanData[ ss ];
5813 
5814  for ( int rr = 0; rr < kcpoint; rr++ )
5815  {
5816  double rvalue = scan->rvalues[ rr ];
5817 
5818  // Protect against possible inf's and nan's, if a reading
5819  // evaluates to 0 or wherever log function is undefined or -inf
5820  if ( rvalue < 1.0 ) rvalue = 1.0;
5821 
5822  // Check for boundary condition
5823  int ndx = qMin( ss, ndxmax );
5824  double prval = ExpData.RIProfile[ ndx ];
5825  scan->rvalues[ rr ] = ( prval != 0.0 ) ?
5826  log10( prval / rvalue ) : 0.0;
5827  }
5828  }
5829 
5830  // Let's mark pseudo-absorbance as different from RI data,
5831  // since it needs some different processing in some places
5832  isPseudo = true;
5833  }
5834 
5835  // Enable intensity plot
5836  referenceDefined = true;
5837  DbgLv(1) << "CGui:PCA: (7)referDef=" << referenceDefined;
5838  pb_intensity->setEnabled( true );
5839  pb_reference->setEnabled( false );
5840  pb_cancelref->setEnabled( true );

5845 //For ABDE: convert to absorbance based on AProfile's ref. chann/use ref. chann defs
5846 void US_ConvertGui::absorbance_conversion_abde( void )
5847 {
5848  data_plot->replot();
5849 
5850  //Map of ref-to-outData
5851  // QMap ref_to_outData< QString("1B232"),US_DataIO::RawData* >
5852  QMap < QString, US_DataIO::RawData > ref_to_outData;
5853  QMap < QString, QString > sample_to_ref;
5854  for ( int ii = 0; ii < outData.size(); ii++)
5855  {
5856  QString cell = QString::number( outData.at(ii)->cell );
5857  QString channame = QString( outData.at(ii)->channel );
5858  QString wvl = QString::number( outData.at(ii)->scanData.at(0).wavelength );
5859 
5860  QString cellchan = cell + channame;
5861  QString cellchanwvl = cellchan + wvl;
5862 
5863  qDebug() << "in absorbance_conversion_abde(): cell, channame, wvl, #, out_triples -- "
5864  << cell << channame << wvl << ii << out_triples[ii];
5865  //Output: in absorbance_conversion_abde(): cell, channame, wvl, #, out_triples -- "3" "B" 290 179 "3 / B / 290"
5866 
5867  if ( channels_abde_refs[ cellchan ] > 0 )
5868  ref_to_outData[ cellchanwvl ] = *(outData[ii]);
5869 
5870  //connect sample & ref by triple name (1A232)
5871  if ( channels_abde_use_refs[ cellchan ] > 0 )
5872  {
5873  int use_ref_num = channels_abde_use_refs[ cellchan ];
5874  QMap<QString, int>::iterator rnr;
5875  for ( rnr = channels_abde_refs.begin(); rnr != channels_abde_refs.end(); ++rnr )
5876  {
5877  if ( rnr.value() == use_ref_num )
5878  {
5879  sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] = rnr.key() + wvl;
5880  break;
5881  }
5882  }
5883 
5884  }
5885  }
5886 
5887  //Debug
5888  qDebug() << "ref_to_outData.keys() -- " << ref_to_outData.keys();
5889  qDebug() << "sample_to_ref.keys() -- " << sample_to_ref.keys();
5890 
5891  //Now, go over outData again:
5892  for ( int ii = 0; ii < outData.size(); ii++)
5893  {
5894  QString cell = QString::number( outData.at(ii)->cell );
5895  QString channame = QString( outData.at(ii)->channel );
5896  QString wvl = QString::number( outData.at(ii)->scanData.at(0).wavelength );
5897 
5898  QString cellchan = cell + channame;
5899  QString cellchanwvl = cellchan + wvl;
5900 
5901  int ns = outData.at(ii)->scanData.size();
5902 
5903  US_DataIO::RawData* currentData = outData[ ii ];
5904  int kcpoint = currentData->pointCount();
5905 
5906  qDebug() << "in absorbance_conversion_abde(): cell, channame, wvl, #, out_triples -- "
5907  << cell << channame << wvl << ii;
5908 
5909  //Set correction vector to itself initially
5910  QVector< QVector<double>> buffer_rvalues;
5911  for ( int ss = 0; ss < currentData->scanCount(); ss++ )
5912  buffer_rvalues << currentData->scanData.at( ss ).rvalues;
5913 
5914  //1. if NOT a reference itself:
5915  if ( sample_to_ref.contains( cellchanwvl ))
5916  {
5917  qDebug() << "Going to convert for triple -- " << cellchanwvl
5918  << "with the reference triple -- " << sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ];
5919 
5920  //Check for matching Scan # in Sample & Ref.
5921  qDebug() << "#Scans: ns_data, ns_ref -- "
5922  << ns << ref_to_outData[ sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] ].scanData.size();
5923 
5924  int ns_min = ns;
5925  if (ns != ref_to_outData[ sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] ].scanData.size())
5926  {
5927  qDebug() << "Number Scans Not Matched!";
5928  ns_min = qMin( ns, ref_to_outData[ sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] ].scanData.size() );
5929  //return;
5930  }
5931 
5932  buffer_rvalues. clear();
5933  for (int nsc = 0; nsc < ns_min; nsc++)
5934  {
5935  buffer_rvalues << ref_to_outData[ sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] ].scanData.at( nsc ).rvalues;
5936  //qDebug() << "Buffer vals [in Correction] " << ref_to_outData[ sample_to_ref[ cellchanwvl ] ].scanData.at( nsc ).rvalues;
5937  }
5938  // }
5939  //2. Refrence itself
5940  // else
5941  // {
5942  // for (int nsc = 0; nsc < ns; nsc++)
5943  // buffer_rvalues << outData.at(ii)->scanData.at( nsc ).rvalues;
5944  // }
5945 
5946  for ( int ss = 0; ss < currentData->scanCount(); ss++ )
5947  {
5948  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &currentData->scanData[ ss ];
5949 
5950  //qDebug() << "buffer_rvalues at log : " << buffer_rvalues.at( ss );
5951 
5952  for ( int rr = 0; rr < kcpoint; rr++ )
5953  {
5954  double rvalue = scan->rvalues[ rr ];
5955  double val = buffer_rvalues.at(ss).at(rr) / rvalue;
5956  if (val <= 0)
5957  val = 1e-5;
5958 
5959  scan->rvalues[ rr ] = std::log10(val);
5960  }
5961  }
5962  }
5963  }
5964 
5965  plot_current();
5966  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5967 
5968  pb_reference ->setEnabled( false );
5969  referenceDefined = true;
5970 
5971  // ALEXEY: just enable Save btn for autoflow
5972  lw_todoinfo->clear();
5973  pb_saveUS3 ->setEnabled( true );
5974  //show_intensity_auto();
5975 
5976  enableRunIDControl( false );
5977 
5978  le_status->setText( tr( "[ABDE] Conversion to Absorbance Completed." ) );
5979  qApp->processEvents();
5980 
5981 }

5984 // Bring up a graph window showing the intensity profile
5985 void US_ConvertGui::show_intensity( void )
5986 {
5987  QString triple = out_triples[ 0 ];
5988  QVector< double > scan_nbrs;
5989 
5990  if ( isMwl )
5991  { // For MWL, set special triple string and build scan numbers
5992  int riscans = ExpData.RI_nscans;
5993  int riwvlns = ExpData.RI_nwvlns;
5994  triple = out_channels[ 0 ] + " / "
5995  + QString::number( ExpData.RIwvlns[ 0 ] ) + "-"
5996  + QString::number( ExpData.RIwvlns[ riwvlns - 1 ] );
5997 
5998  // Scan numbers are composite wavelength.scan
5999  double scndiv = 0.1;
6000  double scnmax = (double)riscans;
6001  double scnfra = scnmax * scndiv;
6002  while ( scnfra > 0.999 )
6003  {
6004  scndiv *= 0.1;
6005  scnfra = scnmax * scndiv;
6006  }
6007 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: show_intensity scndiv scnfra" << scndiv << scnfra;
6008 
6009  for ( int ii = 0; ii < riwvlns; ii++ )
6010  {
6011  double wvbase = (double)ExpData.RIwvlns[ ii ];
6012 
6013  for ( int jj = 0; jj < riscans; jj++ )
6014  {
6015  double scnnbr = wvbase + scndiv * (double)( jj + 1 );
6016  scan_nbrs << scnnbr;
6017  }
6018  }
6019  }
6020 
6021  else
6022  { // For non-MWL, set scan numbers vector
6023  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ExpData.RIProfile.size(); ii++ )
6024  scan_nbrs << (double)( ii + 1 );
6025  }

6556 //Check if triple is the reference one for a channel..
6557 bool US_ConvertGui::isSet_to_edit_triple( QString triple_name )
6558 {
6559  bool isRef = false;
6560 
6561  //In case anaprofile does not have "wvl_edit" attr, so QMap<> triple_to_edit empty (older protocols):
6562  if ( triple_to_edit.isEmpty() )
6563  {
6564  qDebug() << "It looks like older protocol is in use: QMap triple_to_edit is EMPTY!";
6565 
6566  isRef = true;
6567  return isRef;
6568  }
6569 
6570  triple_name.replace( " / ", "." );
6571  QStringList triple_name_list = triple_name.split(".");
6572  QString channel = triple_name_list[0] + triple_name_list[1];
6573  QString wvl = triple_name_list[2];
6574 
6575  QMap<QString, QString>::iterator jj;
6576  for ( jj = triple_to_edit.begin(); jj != triple_to_edit.end(); ++jj )
6577  {
6578  if ( jj.key().contains( channel ) )
6579  {
6580  QString wvl_set_edit = jj.value();
6581 
6582  if ( wvl_set_edit == wvl )
6583  {
6584  qDebug() << "Triple " << triple_name << " for channel " << channel << " is set for EDIT.";
6585  isRef = true;
6586  break;
6587  }
6588  }
6589  }
6590 
6591  return isRef;
6592 }

6594 // Read AProfile info on the reference wvls if Mwl case:
6595 void US_ConvertGui::read_aprofile_data_from_aprofile()
6596 {
6597  channels_to_analyse.clear();
6598  triple_to_edit .clear();
6599  channels_to_drop .clear();
6600  channels_report .clear();
6601 
6602  //ABDE
6603  channels_abde_refs .clear();
6604  channels_abde_use_refs .clear();
6605 
6606  QString aprofile_xml;
6607 
6608  // Check DB connection
6609  US_Passwd pw;
6610  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
6611  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
6612 
6613  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
6614  {
6615  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
6616  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
6617  return;
6618  }
6619 
6620  qDebug() << "AProfGUID: " << AProfileGUID;
6621 
6622 
6623  QStringList qry;
6624  qry << "get_aprofile_info" << AProfileGUID;
6625  db.query( qry );
6626 
6627  while ( db.next() )
6628  {

6644 //Read channel-to-ref_wvl info from AProfile
6645 bool US_ConvertGui::readAProfileBasicParms_auto( QXmlStreamReader& xmli )
6646 {
6647  while( ! xmli.atEnd() )
6648  {
6649  QString ename = xmli.name().toString();
6650 
6651  if ( xmli.isStartElement() )
6652  {
6653  if ( ename == "channel_parms" )
6654  {
6655  QXmlStreamAttributes attr = xmli.attributes();
6656 
6657  if ( attr.hasAttribute("load_volume") ) //ensure it reads upper-level <channel_parms>
6658  {
6659  QString channel_name = attr.value( "channel" ).toString();
6660  QString channel_desc = attr.value( "chandesc" ).toString();
6661 
6662  QString opsys = channel_desc.split(":")[1]; // UV/vis. or Interf.
6663  QString chcell = channel_desc.split(":")[0]; // 1A, 1B...
6664 
6665  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI ) //combined run !
6666  {
6667  if ( opsys.contains("UV/vis") && type_to_process == "RI" )
6668  {
6669  //Read what channels to analyse:
6670  if ( attr.hasAttribute("run") )
6671  channels_to_analyse[ channel_name ] = bool_flag( attr.value( "run" ).toString() );
6672 
6673  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
6674  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
6675  channels_report[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString();
6676 
6677  //Read what triple selected for editing:
6678  if ( attr.hasAttribute("wvl_edit") )
6679  triple_to_edit[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "wvl_edit" ).toString();
6680 
6681  //ABDE
6682  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_reference") )
6683  channels_abde_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_reference").toInt();
6684  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_use_reference") )
6685  channels_abde_use_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_use_reference").toInt();
6686 
6687  }
6688  if ( opsys.contains("Interf") && type_to_process == "IP" )
6689  {
6690  //Read what channels to analyse:
6691  if ( attr.hasAttribute("run") )
6692  channels_to_analyse[ channel_name ] = bool_flag( attr.value( "run" ).toString() );
6693 
6694  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
6695  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
6696  channels_report[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString();
6697 
6698  //Read what triple selected for editing:
6699  if ( attr.hasAttribute("wvl_edit") )
6700  triple_to_edit[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "wvl_edit" ).toString();
6701 
6702  //ABDE
6703  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_reference") )
6704  channels_abde_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_reference").toInt();
6705  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_use_reference") )
6706  channels_abde_use_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_use_reference").toInt();
6707  }
6708  }
6709  else //1-type optics
6710  {
6711  //Read what channels to analyse:
6712  if ( attr.hasAttribute("run") )
6713  channels_to_analyse[ channel_name ] = bool_flag( attr.value( "run" ).toString() );
6714 
6715  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
6716  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
6717  channels_report[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString() ;
6718 
6719  //Read what triple selected for editing:
6720  if ( attr.hasAttribute("wvl_edit") )
6721  triple_to_edit[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "wvl_edit" ).toString();
6722 
6723  //ABDE
6724  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_reference") )
6725  channels_abde_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_reference").toInt();
6726  if ( attr.hasAttribute("abde_use_reference") )
6727  channels_abde_use_refs[ chcell ] = attr.value("abde_use_reference").toInt();
6728  }
6729 
6730  }
6731  }
6732  }
6733 
6734  bool was_end = xmli.isEndElement(); // Just read was End of element?
6735  xmli.readNext(); // Read the next element
6736 
6737  if ( was_end && ename == "p_2dsa" ) // Break
6738  break;
6739  }
6740 
6741  return ( ! xmli.hasError() );
6742 }

6750 int US_ConvertGui::check_for_data_left( QString chann, QString type )
6751 {
6752  int triples_to_exclude = 0;
6753 
6754  if ( type == "channel" )
6755  {
6756  for ( int trx = 0; trx < all_triples.size(); trx++ )
6757  { // Mark matching triples as excluded
6758  QString tchan = QString( all_triples[ trx ] )
6759  .section( "/", 1, 1 ).simplified();
6760 
6761  if ( tchan == chann )
6762  {
6763  ++triples_to_exclude;
6764  }
6765  }
6766  }
6767 
6768  if ( type == "cellchannel" )
6769  {
6770  for ( int trx = 0; trx < all_triples.size(); trx++ )
6771  { // Mark matching triples as excluded
6772  QString tcelchn = QString( all_triples[ trx ] )
6773  .section( "/", 0, 1 ).simplified();
6774 
6775  if ( tcelchn == chann )
6776  {
6777  ++triples_to_exclude;
6778  }
6779  }
6780  }
6781 
6782 
6783  int triples_left = out_triples.size() - triples_to_exclude;
6784 
6785  qDebug() << "In check_for_left_data(): triples_left: " << out_triples.size() << " - " << triples_to_exclude << " = " << triples_left;
6786 
6787  return triples_left;
6788 }

6790 // Drop the triples for the selected channel (all A's or B's) ('Drop All Channel 'A's')
6791 void US_ConvertGui::drop_channel()
6792 {
6793  QString chann = lw_triple->currentItem()->text()
6794  .section( "/", 1, 1 ).simplified(); // "A" or "B"
6795 
6796  //check if there will be any data left && check if AUTO constructor

6798  {
6799  int stat = QMessageBox::warning( this,
6800  tr( "All Data To Be Dropped" ),
6801  tr( "<font color='red'><b>ATTENTION:</b> Are you sure you want to drop all data?</font><br><br>"
6802  "(At least 1 triple is required to proceed to Editing, Analysis & Report stages...)<br><br>"
6803  "If that is what you intend, click <b>\"Proceed\"</b>.<br><br>"
6804  "NOTE: The program will be reset; you will no longer be able to process current run "
6805  "with this program<br>"),
6806  tr( "&Proceed" ), tr( "&Cancel" ) );
6807

6809  return;
6810

6812  delete_autoflow_record();
6813  resetAll_auto();

6815  return;
6816  }

6818

6820  tr( "Drop Triples with Selected Channel" ),
6821  tr( "You have selected a list item that implies you wish to"
6822  " drop triples that have channel '%1'\n\n"
6823  "If that is what you intend, click \"Proceed\".\n\n"
6824  "Otherwise, you should \"Cancel\".\n" ).arg( chann ),
6825  tr( "&Proceed" ), tr( "&Cancel" ) );
6826 
6827  if ( status != 0 ) return;
6828 
6829  //identify all dropped channels

6831  {

6834  {
6835  channels_to_drop[ QString( channel_cell ).replace(" / ","") ] = true;
6836  qDebug() << "DROP All A's/B's: Channel_cell for EXCLUSION -- " << channel_cell;
6837  }
6838  }
6839 
6840  for ( int trx = 0; trx < all_triples.size(); trx++ )
6841  { // Mark matching triples as excluded
6842  QString tchan = QString( all_triples[ trx ] )
6843  .section( "/", 1, 1 ).simplified();
6844 
6845  if ( tchan == chann )
6846  {
6847  all_tripinfo[ trx ].excluded = true;
6848 DbgLv(1) << "DelChan: EXCLUDED chn trx" << chann << trx;
6849  }
6850  }
6851 
6852  //Add small dialog for reason / comment to triples' drop:
6853  if ( us_convert_auto_mode && !usmode )
6854  {
6855  QString t_comment = comment_for_drop_dialog( "channel(s)" );
6856  if ( t_comment. isEmpty() )
6857  return;
6858  else
6859  {
6860  //write t_comment as follows:
6865  drop_operations[ runType ][ "Channels" ] = t_comment;
6866  }
6867  }
6868 
6869 
6870  build_output_data(); // Rebuild the output data controls
6871 
6872  build_lambda_ctrl(); // Rebuild lambda controls
6873 
6874  setTripleInfo(); // Review new triple information
6875 
6876  plot_titles(); // Output a plot of the current data
6877  plot_all();
6878 
6879  //Set correct Solution/Descr/Centerpiece Names
6880  triple_index();
6881  le_description ->setText( outData[ tripDatax ]->description );
6882 
6883  le_solutionDesc->setText( out_chaninfo[ tripListx ].solution.solutionDesc );
6884  le_centerpieceDesc ->setText( out_chaninfo[ tripListx ].centerpieceName );
6885 
6886 }

6889 {

7004 //Read autoflowStages record
7005 int US_ConvertGui::read_autoflow_stages_record( int autoflowID )
7006 {
7007  int status = 0;
7008 
7009  // Check DB connection
7010  US_Passwd pw;
7011  QString masterpw = pw.getPasswd();
7012  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( masterpw );
7013 
7014  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
7015  {
7016  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
7017  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
7018  return status;
7019  }
7020 
7021 
7022  //qDebug() << "BEFORE query ";
7023  QStringList qry;
7024  qry << "autoflow_import_status"
7025  << QString::number( autoflowID );
7026 
7027  status = db->statusQuery( qry );
7028  //qDebug() << "AFTER query ";
7029 
7030  return status;
7031 }

7058 // Query autoflow record
7059 QMap< QString, QString> US_ConvertGui::read_autoflow_record( int autoflowID )
7060 {
7061  // Check DB connection
7062  US_Passwd pw;
7063  QString masterpw = pw.getPasswd();
7064  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( masterpw );
7065 
7066  QMap <QString, QString> protocol_details;
7067 
7068  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
7069  {
7070  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
7071  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
7072  return protocol_details;
7073  }
7074 
7075  QStringList qry;
7076  qry << "read_autoflow_record"
7077  << QString::number( autoflowID );
7078 
7079  db->query( qry );
7080 
7081  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // Autoflow record exists
7082  {
7083  while ( db->next() )
7084  {
7085  protocol_details[ "protocolName" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
7086  protocol_details[ "CellChNumber" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
7087  protocol_details[ "TripleNumber" ] = db->value( 2 ).toString();
7088  protocol_details[ "duration" ] = db->value( 3 ).toString();
7089  protocol_details[ "experimentName" ] = db->value( 4 ).toString();
7090  protocol_details[ "experimentId" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
7091  protocol_details[ "runID" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
7092  protocol_details[ "status" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
7093  protocol_details[ "dataPath" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
7094  protocol_details[ "OptimaName" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
7095  protocol_details[ "runStarted" ] = db->value( 10 ).toString();
7096  protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ] = db->value( 11 ).toString();
7097 
7098  protocol_details[ "correctRadii" ] = db->value( 13 ).toString();
7099  protocol_details[ "expAborted" ] = db->value( 14 ).toString();
7100  protocol_details[ "label" ] = db->value( 15 ).toString();
7101  protocol_details[ "gmpRun" ] = db->value( 16 ).toString();
7102 
7103  protocol_details[ "filename" ] = db->value( 17 ).toString();
7104  protocol_details[ "aprofileguid" ] = db->value( 18 ).toString();
7105 
7106  protocol_details[ "expType" ] = db->value( 26 ).toString();
7107  protocol_details[ "dataSource" ] = db->value( 27 ).toString();
7108  protocol_details[ "opticsFailedType" ] = db->value( 28 ).toString();
7109 
7110  }
7111  }
7112 
7113  return protocol_details;

7808 
7809  //set autoflowStages to "DONE" ?
7810

7812  emit saving_complete_auto( details_at_editing );
7813  }
7814  }
7815  }
7816  }
7817  }
7818  else

7822  tr( "The save of all data and reports is complete." ) );
7823  }

7827 //Record RI or IP status to autoflowStatus
7828 void US_ConvertGui::record_import_status( bool auto_ref, QString runtype )
7829 {
7830  //Check if autoflowStatus record has been created at 2. LIVE_UPDATE already (by remotly SKIP stage &&|| STOP Optima signals):
7831  qDebug() << "autoflowStatusID from 2. LIVE_UPDATE: " << details_at_editing[ "statusID" ];
7832 
7833  autoflowStatusID = 0;
7834  QString importRI_Json;
7835  QString importIP_Json;
7836 
7837  // Check DB connection
7838  US_Passwd pw;
7839  QString masterpw = pw.getPasswd();
7840  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( masterpw );
7841 
7842  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
7843  {
7844  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
7845  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
7846  return;
7847  }
7848 
7849  QStringList qry;
7850 
7851  //get user info
7852  qry.clear();
7853  qry << QString( "get_user_info" );
7854  db->query( qry );
7855  db->next();
7856 
7857  int ID = db->value( 0 ).toInt();
7858  QString fname = db->value( 1 ).toString();
7859  QString lname = db->value( 2 ).toString();
7860  QString email = db->value( 4 ).toString();
7861  int level = db->value( 5 ).toInt();
7862 
7863  qDebug() << "IN US_convert, record RI status: ID,name,email,lev" << ID << fname << lname << email << level;
7864 
7865  //Record to autoflowStatus:
7866  qry.clear();
7867 
7868  //first, check if there is already a record in autoflowStatus with autoflowID == autoflowID_passed;
7869  // that is a scenario for combined RI+IP type
7870  // if there IS record, update it; otherwise create a new one..
7871 
7872  qry << "get_autoflowStatus_id" << QString::number( autoflowID_passed );
7873  autoflowStatusID = db->functionQuery( qry );
7874 
7875  qDebug() << "autoflowStatusID from DB ;; from 2. LIVE_UPDATE: -- "
7876  << autoflowStatusID << " ;; "
7877  << details_at_editing[ "statusID" ];
7878  qDebug() << "runtype -- " << runtype;
7879 
7880  qry.clear();
7881 
7882  if ( runtype == "RI" || runtype == "RA" )
7883  {
7884  QString refScan = auto_ref ? QString("automated") : QString("manual");
7885 
7886  importRI_Json. clear();
7887  importRI_Json += "{ \"Person\": ";
7888 
7889  importRI_Json += "[{";
7890  importRI_Json += "\"ID\":\"" + QString::number( ID ) + "\",";
7891  importRI_Json += "\"fname\":\"" + fname + "\",";
7892  importRI_Json += "\"lname\":\"" + lname + "\",";
7893  importRI_Json += "\"email\":\"" + email + "\",";
7894  importRI_Json += "\"level\":\"" + QString::number( level ) + "\"";
7895  importRI_Json += "}],";
7896 
7897  importRI_Json += "\"RefScan\": \"" + refScan + "\"";
7898 
7899  //Now, add comment from SAVING form:
7900  importRI_Json += ", \"Comment when SAVED\": \"" + gmp_submitter_map[ "Comment:" ] + "\"";
7901 
7902  //Now check if there are comments on dropped {Triples, Channels, Selected Cahnnel}
7903  if ( !drop_operations[ runType ]. isEmpty() )
7904  {
7905  importRI_Json += ", \"Dropped\": ";
7906  importRI_Json += "[{";
7907  QMap<QString, QString>::iterator jj;
7908  for ( jj = drop_operations[ runType ].begin(); jj != drop_operations[ runType ].end(); ++jj )
7909  {
7910  qDebug() << "QMAP: drop_operations[ runType ], key / value -- " << runType << jj.key() << jj.value();
7911  importRI_Json += "\"" + jj.key() + "\": \"" + jj.value() + "\",";
7912  }
7913  importRI_Json.chop(1);
7914  importRI_Json += "}]";
7915  }
7917 
7918  importRI_Json += "}";
7919 
7920  if ( !autoflowStatusID )
7921  {
7922  //create new record
7923  qry << "new_autoflowStatusRI_record"
7924  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
7925  << importRI_Json;
7926 
7927  //qDebug() << "new_autoflowStatusRI_record qry -- " << qry;
7928 
7929  autoflowStatusID = db->functionQuery( qry );
7930  }
7931  else
7932  {
7933  //update
7934  qry << "update_autoflowStatusRI_record"
7935  << QString::number( autoflowStatusID )
7936  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
7937  << importRI_Json;
7938 
7939  db->query( qry );
7940  }
7941  }
7942 
7943  if ( runtype == "IP" )
7944  {
7945  QString refScan = auto_ref ? QString("automated") : QString("manual");
7946 
7947  importIP_Json. clear();
7948  importIP_Json += "{ \"Person\": ";
7949 
7950  importIP_Json += "[{";
7951  importIP_Json += "\"ID\":\"" + QString::number( ID ) + "\",";
7952  importIP_Json += "\"fname\":\"" + fname + "\",";
7953  importIP_Json += "\"lname\":\"" + lname + "\",";
7954  importIP_Json += "\"email\":\"" + email + "\",";
7955  importIP_Json += "\"level\":\"" + QString::number( level ) + "\"";
7956  importIP_Json += "}],";
7957 
7958  importIP_Json += "\"RefScan\": \"" + refScan + "\"";
7959 
7960  //Now, add comment from SAVING form:
7961  importIP_Json += ", \"Comment when SAVED\": \"" + gmp_submitter_map[ "Comment:" ] + "\"";
7962 
7963  //Now check if there are comments on dropped {Triples, Channels, Selected Cahnnel}
7964  if ( !drop_operations[ runType ]. isEmpty() )
7965  {
7966  importIP_Json += ", \"Dropped\": ";
7967  importIP_Json += "[{";
7968  QMap<QString, QString>::iterator jj;
7969  for ( jj = drop_operations[ runType ].begin(); jj != drop_operations[ runType ].end(); ++jj )
7970  {
7971  qDebug() << "QMAP: drop_operations[ runType ], key / value -- " << runType << jj.key() << jj.value();
7972  importIP_Json += "\"" + jj.key() + "\": \"" + jj.value() + "\",";
7973  }
7974  importIP_Json.chop(1);
7975  importIP_Json += "}]";
7976  }
7978 
7979  importIP_Json += "}";
7980 
7981  if ( !autoflowStatusID )
7982  {
7983  //create new record
7984  qry << "new_autoflowStatusIP_record"
7985  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
7986  << importIP_Json;
7987 
7988  autoflowStatusID = db->functionQuery( qry );
7989  }
7990  else
7991  {
7992  //update
7993  qry << "update_autoflowStatusIP_record"
7994  << QString::number( autoflowStatusID )
7995  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
7996  << importIP_Json;
7997 
7998  db->query( qry );
7999  }
8000  }
8001 
8002  if ( !autoflowStatusID )
8003  {
8004  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "AutoflowStatus Record Problem" ),
8005  tr( "autoflowStatus (IMPORT {RI,IP}): There was a problem with creating a record in autoflowStatus table \n" ) + db->lastError() );
8006 
8007  return;
8008  }
8009 
8010  qDebug() << "in record_import_status: importRI_Json,importIP_Json -- " << importRI_Json << "\n" << importIP_Json;
8011 }

8014 //Update autoflow record upon Editing completion
8015 void US_ConvertGui::update_autoflow_record_atLimsImport( void )
8016 {
8017  QString filename_toDB;
8018  //If runType_combined - create a list of runIDs and pass to autoflow...
8019  if ( runType_combined_IP_RI )
8020  filename_toDB = runTypeList.join(",");
8021  else
8022  filename_toDB = runID;
8023 
8024 
8025  details_at_editing[ "filename" ] = filename_toDB;
8026 
8027  // Check DB connection
8028  US_Passwd pw;
8029  QString masterpw = pw.getPasswd();
8030  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( masterpw );
8031 
8032  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
8033  {
8034  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
8035  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
8036  return;
8037  }
8038 
8039  QStringList qry;
8040 
8041  //now, make a record in the autoflowIntensity table, return ID
8042  int autoflowIntensityID = 0;
8043  qDebug() << "[in update_autoflow_record_atLimsImport()] intensityJsonRI -- " << intensityJsonRI;
8044  if ( ! intensityJsonRI.isEmpty() )
8045  {
8046  qry.clear();
8047  qry << "new_autoflow_intensity_record"
8048  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
8049  << intensityJsonRI;
8050 
8051  qDebug() << "qry new_autoflow_intensity_record -- " << qry;
8052 
8053  autoflowIntensityID = db->functionQuery( qry );
8054  qDebug() << "[after qry] autoflowIntensityID -- " << autoflowIntensityID;
8055 
8056  if ( !autoflowIntensityID || autoflowIntensityID == 0 || autoflowIntensityID < 1 )
8057  {
8058  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "AutoflowIntensity Record Problem" ),
8059  tr( "autoflowIntensity: There was a problem with creating a record in autoflowIntensity table \n" ) + db->lastError() );
8060 
8061  return;
8062  }
8063  }
8064  qDebug() << "autoflowIntensityID -- " << autoflowIntensityID;
8065  details_at_editing[ "intensityID" ] = QString::number( autoflowIntensityID );
8066 
8067 
8068  //Now check if autoflowStatus record was created:
8069  if ( !autoflowStatusID )
8070  {
8071  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "AutoflowStatus Record Problem" ),
8072  tr( "autoflowStatus (IMPORT {RI,IP}): There was a problem with creating a record in autoflowStatus table \n" ) );
8073 
8074  return;
8075  }
8076  qDebug() << "autoflowStatusID -- " << autoflowStatusID;
8077  details_at_editing[ "statusID" ] = QString::number( autoflowStatusID );
8078 
8079 
8080  //finally, update autoflow record
8081  qry.clear();
8082  // qry << "update_autoflow_at_lims_import"
8083  // << runID_numeric
8084  // << filename_toDB
8085  // << OptimaName
8086  // << QString::number( autoflowIntensityID )
8087  // << QString::number( autoflowStatusID );
8088 
8089  qry << "update_autoflow_at_lims_import"
8090  << filename_toDB
8091  << QString::number( autoflowIntensityID )
8092  << QString::number( autoflowStatusID )
8093  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed );
8094 
8095  qDebug() << "Query for update_autoflow_at_lims_import -- " << qry;
8096  //db->query( qry );
8097 
8098  int status = db->statusQuery( qry );
8099 
8100  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_AUTOFLOW_RECORD )
8101  {
8102  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8103  tr( "Autoflow Record Not Updated" ),
8104  tr( "No autoflow record\n"
8105  "associated with this experiment." ) );
8106  return;
8107  }
8108 }

8155 // Save to disk (default directory)
8156 int US_ConvertGui::saveUS3Disk( void )
8157 {
8158  if ( allData[ 0 ].scanData.empty() ) return US_Convert::NODATA;
8159 
8160  QDir writeDir( US_Settings::resultDir() );
8161  QString dirname = writeDir.absolutePath() + "/" + runID + "/";
8162 
8163  if ( !us_convert_auto_mode )
8164  {
8165  if ( saveStatus == NOT_SAVED &&
8166  writeDir.exists( runID ) )
8167  {
8168  QMessageBox::information( this,
8169  tr( "Error" ),
8170  tr( "The write directory, " ) + dirname +
8171  tr( " already exists. Please change run ID to a unique value." ) );
8172  return US_Convert::DUP_RUNID;
8173  }
8174  }
8175 
8176  if ( ! writeDir.exists( runID ) )
8177  {
8178  if ( ! writeDir.mkpath( dirname ) )
8179  {
8180  QMessageBox::information( this,
8181  tr( "Error" ),
8182  tr( "Cannot write to " ) + writeDir.absolutePath() );
8183  return US_Convert::CANTOPEN;
8184  }
8185  }
8186 
8187  int status;
8188 
8189  // Check to see if we have all the data to write
8190  if ( ! ExpData.syncOK )
8191  {
8192  status = QMessageBox::information( this,
8193  tr( "Warning" ),
8194  tr( "The run has not yet been associated with the database."
8195  " Click 'OK' to proceed anyway, or click 'Cancel'"
8196  " and then click on the 'Edit Run Information'"
8197  " button to enter this information first.\n" ),
8198  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
8199  0, 0, 1 );
8200  if ( status != 0 ) return US_Convert::NOT_WRITTEN;
8201  }
8202 
8203  // Write the data
8204  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving data to disk ..." ) );
8205  qApp->processEvents();
8206  bool saveGUIDs = saveStatus != NOT_SAVED;
8207  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8208 
8209  status = US_Convert::saveToDisk( outData, out_tripinfo, allExcludes,
8210  runType, runID, dirname, saveGUIDs );
8211 
8212  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8213 
8214  // Now try to write the xml file
8215  status = ExpData.saveToDisk( out_tripinfo, runType, runID, dirname,
8216  speedsteps );
8217 
8218  qDebug() << "saveDisk: xml status -- " << status;
8219 
8220  // How many files should have been written?
8221  int fileCount = out_tripinfo.size();
8222 DbgLv(1) << "SV: fileCount" << fileCount;
8223 
8224  // Now try to communicate status
8225  if ( status == US_Convert::CANTOPEN )
8226  {
8227  QString writeFile = runID + "."
8228  + runType + ".xml";
8229  QMessageBox::information( this,
8230  tr( "Error" ),
8231  tr( "Cannot open write file: " ) + dirname + writeFile );
8232  }
8233 
8234  else if ( status == US_Convert::NOXML )
8235  {
8236  // Main xml data is missing
8237  QMessageBox::information( this,
8238  tr( "Warning" ),
8239  tr( "The run information file was not written. "
8240  "Please click on the "
8241  "'Associate Run with DB' button \n\n " ) +
8242  QString::number( fileCount ) + " " +
8243  runID + tr( " files written." ) );
8244  return( status );
8245  }
8246 
8247  else if ( status == US_Convert::PARTIAL_XML )
8248  {
8249  // xml data is missing for one or more triples
8250  QMessageBox::information( this,
8251  tr( "Warning" ),
8252  tr( "Solution information is incomplete. Please click on the "
8253  "'Manage Solutions' button for each "
8254  "cell, channel, and wavelength combination \n\n " ) +
8255  QString::number( fileCount ) + " "
8256  + runID + tr( " files written." ) );
8257  return( status );
8258  }
8259 
8260  else if ( status != US_Convert::OK )
8261  {
8262  QMessageBox::information( this,
8263  tr( "Error" ),
8264  tr( "Error: " ) + status );
8265  return( status );
8266  }
8267 
8268  // Save or delete RI intensity profile
8269  if ( runType == "RI" )
8270  {
8271  if ( referenceDefined )
8272  {
8273  status = ExpData.saveRIDisk( runID, dirname );
8274  qDebug() << "SV: saveRIDisk status" << status;
8275 
8276  if ( status == US_Convert::CANTOPEN )
8277  {
8278  QString writeFile = runID + "."
8279  + "RIProfile.xml";
8280  QMessageBox::information( this,
8281  tr( "Error" ),
8282  tr( "Cannot open write file: " ) + dirname + writeFile );
8283  }
8284 
8285  else if ( status != US_Convert::OK )
8286  {
8287  QMessageBox::information( this,
8288  tr( "Error" ),
8289  tr( "Error: " ) + status );
8290  return( status );
8291 
8292  }
8293  }
8294 else
8295 DbgLv(1) << "SV: NO saveRIDisk : refDef" << referenceDefined;
8296 
8297  else
8298  {
8299  // Maybe the profile has been deleted, so let's
8300  // delete the xml file and avoid confusion later
8301  QDir d( dirname );
8302  QString filename = runID + "."
8303  + "RIProfile.xml";
8304  if ( d.exists( filename ) && ! d.remove( filename ) )
8305  qDebug() << "Unable to remove file" << filename;
8306 
8307  }
8308  }
8309 else
8310 DbgLv(1) << "SV: NO saveRIDisk : runType" << runType;
8311 
8312 
8313  // Insure that we have a TimeState record locally for this run
8314  le_status->setText( tr( "Writing Time State to disk..." ) );
8315  if ( writeTimeStateDisk() == 0 )
8316  { // Abort if unable to open TimeState file
8317 
8318  qDebug() << "IN saveUS3Disk(): QUITING HERE !!!!";
8319  return US_Convert::CANTOPEN;
8320  }
8321  fileCount += 2;
8322 
8323  // Status is OK
8324  le_status->setText( tr( "%1 %2 files were written to disk." )
8325  .arg( fileCount ).arg( runID ) );
8326  qApp->processEvents();
8327 
8328  if ( saveStatus == NOT_SAVED )
8329  saveStatus = HD_ONLY;
8330 
8331  // If we are here, it's ok to sync with DB
8332  ExpData.syncOK = true;
8333 
8334  enableRunIDControl( false );
8335 
8336  if ( isMwl )
8337  { // Where triples were expanded for MWL, skip plot save
8338  return( US_Convert::OK );
8339  }
8340 
8341  // Save the main plots
8342  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8343  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving plot and report files ..." ) );
8344  qApp->processEvents();
8345  QString dir = US_Settings::reportDir() + "/" + runID;
8346  if ( ! QDir( dir ).exists() ) // make sure the directory exists
8347  QDir().mkdir( dir );
8348  data_plot->setVisible( false );
8349  int save_tripListx = tripListx;
8350 
8351  // Make sure directory is empty
8352  QDir d( dir );
8353  QStringList rmvfilt;
8354  rmvfilt << "*.svgz" << "*.png" << "*.svg";
8355  QStringList rmvfiles = d.entryList( rmvfilt, QDir::Files, QDir::Name );
8356 
8357  for ( int ii = 0; ii < rmvfiles.size(); ii++ )
8358  if ( ! d.remove( rmvfiles[ ii ] ) )
8359 DbgLv(1) << "Unable to remove file" << rmvfiles[ ii ];
8360 
8361  for ( int ii = 0; ii < out_tripinfo.size(); ii++ )
8362  {
8363  tripListx = ii;
8364 
8365  QString t = out_tripinfo[ ii ].tripleDesc;
8366  QStringList parts = t.split(" / ");
8367 
8368  QString cell = parts[ 0 ];
8369  QString channel = parts[ 1 ];
8370  QString wl = parts[ 2 ];
8371 
8372  QString triple = "";
8373 
8374  if ( runType == "WA" )
8375  {
8376  double r = wl.toDouble() * 1000.0;
8377  QString radius = QString::number( (int) round( r ) );
8378  triple = cell + channel + radius;
8379  }
8380 
8381  else
8382  {
8383  triple = cell + channel + wl;
8384  }
8385 
8386  QString filename = dir + "/cnvt." + triple + ".raw.svgz";
8387 
8388  // Redo current plot and write it to a file
8389  lw_triple->setCurrentRow( tripListx );
8390  plot_current();
8391  int status = US_GuiUtil::save_plot( filename, data_plot );
8392  if ( status != 0 )
8393  qDebug() << filename << "plot not saved";
8394  }
8395 
8396  // Restore original plot
8397  tripListx = save_tripListx;
8398  lw_triple->setCurrentRow( tripListx );
8399  plot_current();
8400  data_plot->setVisible( true );
8401  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving of plot files IS COMPLETE." ) );
8402  qApp->processEvents();
8403  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8404  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8405 
8406  return( US_Convert::OK );
8407 }

8409 // Save to Database
8410 void US_ConvertGui::saveUS3DB( void )
8411 {
8412 
8413  // Verify connectivity
8414  US_Passwd pw;
8415  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
8416  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
8417 
8418  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
8419  {
8420  QMessageBox::information( this,
8421  tr( "Error" ),
8422  tr( "Database connectivity error" ) );
8423 
8424  return;
8425  }
8426 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: (1)trip0tripFilename" << out_tripinfo[0].tripleFilename;
8427 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: tripleGUID "
8428  << US_Util::uuid_unparse((uchar*)out_tripinfo[0].tripleGUID);
8429 
8430  // Ok, let's make sure they know what'll happen
8431  if ( saveStatus == BOTH )

8434  {
