8437  tr( "This will overwrite the raw data currently in the " ) +
8438  tr( "database, and all existing edit profiles, models " ) +
8439  tr( "and noise data will be deleted too. Proceed? " ),
8440  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
8441  0, 0, 1 );
8442  if ( status != 0 ) return;
8443  }
8444  }
8445 
8446  else
8447  {
8448  if ( !us_convert_auto_mode )
8449  {
8450  int status = QMessageBox::information( this,
8451  tr( "Warning" ),
8452  tr( "Once this data is written to the DB you will not " ) +
8453  tr( "be able to make changes to it without erasing the " ) +
8454  tr( "edit profiles, models and noise files too. Proceed? " ),
8455  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
8456  0, 0, 1 );
8457  if ( status != 0 ) return;
8458  }
8459  else
8460  {
8461  // QMessageBox::information( this,
8462  // tr( "Warning" ),
8463  // tr( "Once this data is written to the DB you will not " ) +
8464  // tr( "be able to make changes to it without erasing the " ) +
8465  // tr( "edit profiles, models and noise files too...\n " ) );
8466  }
8467  }
8468 
8469  // First check some of the data with the DB
8470  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8471  le_status->setText( tr( "Preparing Save with DB check ..." ) );
8472  qApp->processEvents();
8473 
8474  qDebug() << "BEFORE checkDiskData(): ExpData.invID = " << ExpData.invID;
8475 
8476  int status;
8477 
8478  if ( us_convert_auto_mode )
8479  status = US_ConvertIO::checkDiskData_auto( ExpData, out_tripinfo, &db );
8480  else
8481  status = US_ConvertIO::checkDiskData( ExpData, out_tripinfo, &db );
8482 
8483  qDebug() << "AFTER checkDiskData(): ExpData.invID = " << ExpData.invID;
8484 
8485  qDebug() << "Status from SaveUs3DB" << status;
8486  // Save a flag for need to repeat the disk write later
8487  bool repeat_disk = ( status == US_DB2::NO_RAWDATA );
8488 
8489  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8490 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: (2)trip0tripFilename" << out_tripinfo[0].tripleFilename;
8491 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: dset tripleID " << out_tripinfo[0].tripleID;
8492 
8493  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_PERSON ) // Investigator or operator doesn't exist
8494  {
8495  QMessageBox::information( this,
8496  tr( "Error" ),
8497  tr( "This investigator or instrument operator was not found\n"
8498  "in the database.\n" ) );
8499  return;
8500  }
8501 
8502  if ( status == US_DB2::BADGUID )
8503  {
8504  QString errmsg;
8505  if ( ExpData.operatorGUID.isEmpty() ||
8506  ExpData.operatorGUID.length() != 36 )
8507  {
8508  errmsg = tr( "Bad Operator GUID format.\n"
8509  "Use LIMS Admin Info -> Edit User Info\n"
8510  "to insure all instruments are permitted\n"
8511  "for at least one user.\n\n"
8512  "Contact UltraScan support for guidance." );
8513  }
8514  else
8515  {
8516  errmsg = tr( "Bad GUID format.\n"
8517  "Please click on Edit Run Information"
8518  " and re-select hardware.\n" );
8519  }
8520  QMessageBox::information( this, tr( "Error" ), errmsg );
8521  return;
8522  }
8523 
8524  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_ROTOR )
8525  {
8526  QMessageBox::information( this,
8527  tr( "Error" ),
8528  tr( "Don't recognize the rotor configuration.\n"
8529  "Please click on Edit Run Information"
8530  " and re-select hardware.\n") );
8531  return;
8532  }
8533 
8534  if ( status != US_DB2::OK && status != US_DB2::NO_RAWDATA )
8535  {
8536  // US_DB2::OK means we're updating; US_DB2::NO_RAWDATA means it's new
8537  QMessageBox::information( this,
8538  tr( "Error" ),
8539  db.lastError() + " (" + db.lastErrno() + ")\n" );
8540  return;
8541  }
8542 
8543  // Save updated files and prepare to transfer to DB
8544  le_status->setText( tr( "Preparing Save with Disk write ..." ) );
8545  qApp->processEvents();
8546 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: (2)dset tripleID " << out_tripinfo[0].tripleID;
8547 
8548 
8549  qDebug() << "BEFORE saveUS3Disk(): ExpData.invID = " << ExpData.invID;
8550 
8551  status = saveUS3Disk();
8552  qDebug() << "DBSv: Status after saveUS3Disk()" << status;
8553 
8554  qDebug() << "AFTER saveUS3Disk(): ExpData.invID = " << ExpData.invID;
8555 
8556  if ( status != US_Convert::OK )
8557  {
8558  qDebug() << "Status : " << status; //HERE it prematurely quits!!! Cannot write timestamp to DISK
8559  return;
8560  }

8562

8566  QDir resultDir( US_Settings::resultDir() );
8567  QString dir = resultDir.absolutePath() + "/" + ExpData.runID + "/";
8568 
8569  if ( ! resultDir.exists( ExpData.runID ) )
8570  {

8572  tr( "Error" ),
8573  tr( "Cannot read from " ) + dir ); // aucDir.absolutePath() );
8574  return;

8580

8582  QDir::Files | QDir::Readable, QDir::Name );
8583 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: files count" << files.size();
8584

8589  tr( "There were no files of the form *.auc\n"
8590  "found in the specified directory." ) );
8591  return;
8592  }
8593

8595  {

8597  {

8600  tr( "The program advanced or is advancing to the next stage!\n\n"

8603  "session and the program proceeded to the next stage. \n\n"
8604  "The program will return to the autoflow runs dialog where "
8605  "you can re-attach to the actual current stage of the run. "
8606  "Please allow some time for the status to be updated.") );
8607 
8608  dataSavedOtherwise = true;
8609  resetAll_auto();
8610  emit saving_complete_back_to_initAutoflow();
8611  return;
8612  }
8613  else
8614  {
8615  // Then the user is trying to overwrite a runID that is already in the DB
8616  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8617  tr( "Duplicate runID" ),
8618  tr( "This runID already exists in the database. To edit that "
8619  "run information, load it from there to begin with.\n" ) );
8620  return;
8621  }
8622  }
8623 
8624  // If saveStatus == BOTH already, then it came from the db to begin with
8625  // and it should be updated. Otherwise, there shouldn't be any database
8626  // records with this runID found
8627  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8628  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving Experiment to DB ..." ) );
8629  qApp->processEvents();
8630 
8631  qDebug() << "SAVE to DB - Initiation!! us_convert_auto_mode = " << us_convert_auto_mode;

8633  {

8636  }
8637  else
8638  {

8640  status = ExpData.saveToDB( ( saveStatus == BOTH ), &db, speedsteps );
8641  }
8642  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8643 
8644  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_PROJECT )
8645  {
8646  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8647  tr( "Project missing" ),
8648  tr( "The project associated with this experiment could not be "
8649  "updated or added to the database.\n" ) );
8650  return;
8651  }
8652 
8653  else if ( status == US_DB2::DUPFIELD )
8654  {
8655  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8656  tr( "Duplicate runID" ),
8657  tr( "The runID already exists in the database.\n" ) );
8658  return;
8659  }
8660

8662  {

8665  tr( "Bad RI XML" ),
8666  tr( "There was a problem with the xml data"
8667  " read from the database.\n" ) );
8668  }
8669

8671  {
8672  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8673  tr( "Problem saving experiment information" ),

8675  + QString::number( status ) + ")" );
8676  return;
8677  }
8678 
8679  // If the data came from the database in the first place,
8680  // then this function erases all the edit profiles, models
8681  // and noise files in the database too. However, if one
8682  // changes most of the things here ( solution, rotor, etc. )
8683  // it would invalidate the data anyway.
8684  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8685  le_status->setText( tr( "Writing raw data to DB ..." ) );
8686  qApp->processEvents();
8687 
8688  QString writeStatus =
8689  US_ConvertIO::writeRawDataToDB( ExpData, out_tripinfo, dir, &db );
8690 
8691  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8692

8694  {
8695  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8696  tr( "Problem saving experiment" ),
8697  tr( "Unspecified database error: " ) + writeStatus );
8698  le_status->setText( tr( "*ERROR* Problem saving experiment." ) );
8699  return;
8700  }
8701

8703  { // Last disk save did not have tripleID values, so update files

8705  le_status->setText( tr( "Writing updated Raw records to disk..." ) );
8706 
8707  status = saveUS3Disk();
8708 
8709  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8710  qApp->processEvents();
8711 DbgLv(1) << "DBSv: REPEAT disk save for raw IDs";
8712  }
8713 
8714  // Insure that we have a TimeState record in the DB for this run
8715  le_status->setText( tr( "Writing Time State to DB..." ) );
8716  writeTimeStateDB();
8717 
8718  le_status->setText( tr( "DB data save complete. Saving reports..." ) );
8719  qApp->processEvents();
8720  saveStatus = BOTH;
8721  enableRunIDControl( false );
8722 
8723  //ALEXEY <- Proceeds here OK! Problem below with saveReportsToDB()
8724 
8725  saveReportsToDB();
8726  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8727  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8728 
8729  le_status->setText( tr( "DB data and reports save IS COMPLETE." ) );
8730  qApp->processEvents();
8731 }

8733 void US_ConvertGui::saveReportsToDB( void )
8734 {
8735  if ( isMwl )
8736  return;
8737 
8738  // Verify connectivity
8739  US_Passwd pw;
8740  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
8741  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
8742 
8743  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
8744  {
8745  QMessageBox::information( this,
8746  tr( "Error" ),
8747  tr( "Database connectivity error" ) );
8748 
8749  return;
8750  }
8751 
8752  // Get a list of report files produced by us_convert
8753  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
8754  QString dir = US_Settings::reportDir() + "/" + runID;
8755  QDir d( dir, "cnvt*", QDir::Name, QDir::Files | QDir::Readable );
8756  d.makeAbsolute();
8757  QStringList files = d.entryList( QDir::Files );
8758 
8759  // Add any run details files to it
8760  QDir d2( dir, "rundetail*", QDir::Name, QDir::Files | QDir::Readable );
8761  d2.makeAbsolute();
8762  files << d2.entryList( QDir::Files );
8763 
8764  // Create US_Report object
8765  QString now = QDateTime::currentDateTime().toString();
8766  US_Report myReport;
8767  myReport.reset();
8768  myReport.runID = runID;
8769  myReport.title = runID + " Report";
8770  myReport.html = "<p>Report created " + now + "</p>";
8771 
8772  // Save all us_convert report files to the DB
8773  QString errorMsg = "";
8774  foreach( QString file, files )
8775  {
8776  // Get description info for the correct triple
8777  QStringList parts = file.split( "." );
8778  QString fileTriple = US_Util::expanded_triple( parts[ 1 ], true );
8779 
8780  // Match the triple to find the correct description in memory
8781  QString description = QString( "" );
8782  for ( int ii = 0; ii < out_tripinfo.size(); ii++ )
8783  {
8784  if ( fileTriple == out_tripinfo[ ii ].tripleDesc )
8785  {
8786  description = outData[ ii ]->description;
8787  break;
8788  }
8789  }
8790 
8791  // Edit data ID is not known yet, so use 1. It goes in the report document
8792  // table itself, so we're not overwriting anything.
8793 
8794  US_Report::Status status;
8795  if ( us_convert_auto_mode )
8796  {
8797  qDebug() << "SAVING Reports in AUTO mode !!";
8798  status = myReport.saveDocumentFromFile_auto( ExpData.invID, dir, file, &db, 1, description );
8799  }
8800  else
8801  status = myReport.saveDocumentFromFile( dir, file, &db, 1, description );
8802 
8803 
8804  if ( status != US_Report::REPORT_OK )
8805  {
8806  errorMsg += file + " was not saved to report database; error code: "
8807  + QString::number( status ) + "\n";
8808  qDebug() << "US_ConvertGui.saveDocumentFromFile error: "
8809  << db.lastError() << db.lastErrno();
8810  }
8811  }
8812  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
8813 
8814  if ( ! errorMsg.isEmpty() )
8815  {
8816  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8817  tr( "Problem saving reports to DB" ),
8818  errorMsg );
8819  }
8820 
8821 }

8842  if ( dir.right( 1 ) != "/" ) dir += "/"; // Ensure trailing "/"
8843

8845  QString new_runID = dir.section( "/", -2, -2 );
8846  QRegExp rx( "[^A-Za-z0-9_-]" );
8847

8850  while ( ( pos = rx.indexIn( new_runID ) ) != -1 )

8856  << "rID_chgd" << runID_changed;

8860  {
8861  QMessageBox::warning( this,
8862  tr( "RunID Name Changed" ),
8863  tr( "The runID name has been changed. It may consist only"
8864  "of alphanumeric \n"
8865  " characters, the underscore, and the hyphen. New runID: " )
8866  + new_runID );
8867  }
8868 
8869  // Set the runID and directory
8870  runID = new_runID;
8871  le_runID ->setText( runID );
8872  le_runID2->setText( runID );
8873  le_dir ->setText( dir );
8874  currentDir = QString( dir );
8875

8877  QStringList nameFilters = QStringList( "*" );
8878  QStringList files = readDir.entryList( nameFilters,
8879  QDir::Files | QDir::Readable, QDir::Name );
8880 
8881  QString tmstFname;
8882  QString txmlFname;
8883  int nauc = 0;
8884  int nmwrs = 0;
8885  int nother = 0;
8886  int ntmst = 0;
8887  int ntxml = 0;
8888  int ntotf = files.size();
8889 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:gI: ntotf" << ntotf;
8890 
8891  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ntotf; jj++ )
8892  {
8893  QString fname = files[ jj ];
8894 
8895  if ( fname.endsWith( ".mwrs" ) )
8896  nmwrs++;
8897 
8898  else if ( fname.endsWith( ".auc" ) )
8899  nauc++;
8900 
8901  else if ( fname.endsWith( "time_state.xml" ) )
8902  {
8903  ntxml++;
8904  txmlFname = fname;
8905  }
8906  else if ( fname.endsWith( "time_state.tmst" ) )
8907  {
8908  ntmst++;
8909  tmstFname = fname;
8910  }
8911  else
8912  nother++;
8913  }
8914 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:gI: nmwrs nauc ntxml ntmst nother"
8915  << nmwrs << nauc << ntxml << ntmst << nother;
8916 
8917  if ( nmwrs > 0 )
8918  jmpType = 1; // Flag import of MWL data
8919 
8920  else if ( nauc > 0 )
8921  jmpType = 2; // Flag import of AUC data
8922 
8923  else
8924  jmpType = 0; // Flag import of Beckman Raw
8925 
8926 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:gI: RTN jmpType" << jmpType;
8927  return jmpType;
8928 }

9056 bool US_ConvertGui::convert( void )
9057 {
9058 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:CV: IN";
9059  // Set tolerance to stay between wl numbers
9060  double tolerance = (double)ct_tolerance->value();
9061 
9062  // Convert the data
9063  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
9064  US_Convert::convertLegacyData( legacyData, allData, all_tripinfo,
9065  runType, tolerance );
9066  int kadata = allData .size();
9067  int katrip = all_tripinfo.size();
9068 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:CV: kadata katrip runType" << kadata << katrip << runType;
9069  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
9070 
9071  if ( kadata == 0 ) return( false );
9072 
9073  le_description->setText( allData[ 0 ].description );
9074  saveDescription = QString( allData[ 0 ].description );
9075 
9076  // Now let's show the user the first one
9077  tripListx = -1;
9078  for ( int ii = 0; ii < katrip; ii++ )
9079  {
9080  if ( all_tripinfo[ ii ].excluded ) continue;
9081 
9082  if ( tripListx == -1 ) tripListx = ii;
9083 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:CV: ii, trip" << ii << all_tripinfo[ii].tripleDesc;
9084  }
9085 
9086 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:CV: RTN tLx" << tripListx << "katrip" << katrip;
9087  return( true );
9088 }

9100 // Function to get abstractCenterpiece names from DB
9101 bool US_ConvertGui::centerpieceInfoDB( void )
9102 {
9103  // Verify connectivity
9104  US_Passwd pw;
9105  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
9106  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
9107 
9108  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
9109  {
9110  QMessageBox::information( this,
9111  tr( "Error" ),
9112  tr( "Database connectivity error" ) );
9113 
9114  return( false );
9115  }
9116 
9117  QStringList q( "get_abstractCenterpiece_names" );
9118  db.query( q );
9119 
9120  QList<listInfo> options;
9121  while ( db.next() )
9122  {
9123  struct listInfo option;
9124  option.ID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
9125  option.text = db.value( 1 ).toString();
9126  options << option;
9127  }
9128 
9129  cb_centerpiece->clear();
9130  if ( options.size() > 0 )
9131  cb_centerpiece->addOptions( options );
9132 
9133 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: centpInfoDB RTN";
9134  return true;
9135 }
9136 
9137 // Function to get abstractCenterpiece names from disk
9138 bool US_ConvertGui::centerpieceInfoDisk( void )
9139 {
9140  // First figure out the xml file name, and try to open it
9141  QFile f( US_Settings::appBaseDir() + "/etc/abstractCenterpieces.xml" );
9142 
9143  if ( ! f.open( QIODevice::ReadOnly ) ) return false;
9144 
9145  QList<listInfo> options;
9146  QXmlStreamReader xml( &f );
9147  while ( ! xml.atEnd() )
9148  {
9149  xml.readNext();
9150 
9151  if ( xml.isStartElement() )
9152  {
9153  if ( xml.name() == "abstractCenterpiece" )
9154  {
9155  struct listInfo option;
9156  QXmlStreamAttributes a = xml.attributes();
9157  option.ID = a.value("id").toString();
9158  option.text = a.value("name").toString();
9159  options << option;
9160  }
9161  }
9162  }
9163 
9164  bool error = xml.hasError();
9165  f.close();
9166 
9167  if ( error ) return false;
9168 
9169  cb_centerpiece->clear();
9170  if ( options.size() > 0 )
9171  {
9172  // Let's sort them so they come up like the DB
9173  for ( int i = 0; i < options.size() - 1; i++ )
9174  for ( int j = i + 1; j < options.size(); j++ )
9175  if ( options[ i ].text > options[ j ].text )
9176  options.swap( i, j );
9177 
9178  cb_centerpiece->addOptions( options );
9179  }
9180 
9181 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: centpInfoDk RTN";
9182  return true;
9183 }

9239  }

9245  }

9251  }
9252

9281 
9282 void US_ConvertGui::plot_all( void )
9283 {
9284  US_DataIO::RawData* currentData = outData[ tripDatax ];
9285 DbgLv(1) << " PlAll: outData count" << outData.count() << "tripDatax" << tripDatax;
9286 
9287  QList< QColor > mcolors;
9288  int nmcols = usplot->map_colors( mcolors );
9289 DbgLv(1) << " PlAll: nmcols" << nmcols;
9290  dataPlotClear( data_plot );
9291  grid = us_grid( data_plot );
9292  int kcpoint = currentData->pointCount();
9293  int kcscan = currentData->scanCount();
9294  QPen pen_plot( US_GuiSettings::plotCurve() );
9295  if ( nmcols == 1 )
9296  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ 0 ] );
9297 
9298  QVector< double > rvec( kcpoint );
9299  QVector< double > vvec( kcpoint );
9300 
9301  double* rr = rvec.data();
9302  double* vv = vvec.data();
9303 
9304  double maxR = -1.0e99;
9305  double minR = 1.0e99;
9306  double maxV = -1.0e99;
9307  double minV = 1.0e99;
9308 
9309  for ( int ii = 0; ii < kcscan; ii++ )
9310  {
9311  US_Convert::Excludes currentExcludes = allExcludes[ tripDatax ];
9312  if ( currentExcludes.contains( ii ) ) continue;
9313  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &currentData->scanData[ ii ];
9314 
9315  for ( int jj = 0; jj < kcpoint; jj++ )
9316  {
9317  rr[ jj ] = currentData->radius( jj );
9318  vv[ jj ] = scan->rvalues[ jj ];
9319 
9320 #if QT_VERSION < 0x050000
9321  if ( vv[ jj ] > 1.0e99 || isnan( vv[ jj ] ) )
9322 #else
9323  if ( vv[ jj ] > 1.0e99 || vv[ jj ] != vv[ jj ] )
9324 #endif
9325  {
9326  // For some reason vv[jj] is going off the scale
9327  // Don't know why, but filter out for now
9328  if ( jj < 5 || ( jj + 5 ) > kcpoint )
9329  qDebug() << "(rr, vv) = ( " << rr[jj] << ", " << vv[jj] << ")"
9330  << " (minR, maxR) = ( " << minR << ", " << maxR << ")" << endl
9331  << " (minV, maxV) = ( " << minV << ", " << maxV << ")" << endl;
9332  continue;
9333  }
9334 
9335  maxR = qMax( maxR, rr[ jj ] );
9336  minR = qMin( minR, rr[ jj ] );
9337  maxV = qMax( maxV, vv[ jj ] );
9338  minV = qMin( minV, vv[ jj ] );
9339  }
9340 
9341  QString title = tr( "Raw Data at " )
9342  + QString::number( scan->seconds ) + tr( " seconds" );
9343 
9344  QwtPlotCurve* curv = us_curve( data_plot, title );
9345  if ( nmcols > 1 )
9346  {
9347  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ ii % nmcols ] );
9348 DbgLv(2) << " PlAll: ii" << ii << "pen_plot" << pen_plot;
9349  }
9350  curv->setPen ( pen_plot );
9351  curv->setSamples( rr, vv, kcpoint );
9352 
9353  }
9354 
9355  // Reset the scan curves within the new limits
9356  double padR = ( maxR - minR ) / 30.0;
9357  double padV = ( maxV - minV ) / 30.0;
9358 
9359  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft , minV - padV, maxV + padV );
9360  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, minR - padR, maxR + padR );
9361 
9362  show_plot_progress = false;
9363  data_plot->replot();
9364 }

9367 {
9368  plot_all();
9369 }

9371 void US_ConvertGui::set_colors( const QList< int >& focus )
9372 {

9374  QwtPlotItemList list = data_plot->itemList();
9375  QList< QwtPlotCurve* > curves;
9376

9378  {

9380  curves << dynamic_cast< QwtPlotCurve* >( list[ i ] );
9381  }
9382 
9383  QPen p = curves[ 0 ]->pen();
9384  QBrush b = curves[ 0 ]->brush();
9385 
9386  // Mark these scans in red
9387  for ( int i = 0; i < curves.size(); i++ )
9388  {
9389  if ( focus.contains( i ) )
9390  {
9391  p.setColor( Qt::red );
9392  curves[ i ]->setPen ( p );
9393  curves[ i ]->setBrush( b );
9394  }
9395  }
9396 
9397  data_plot->replot();
9398 }

9400 void US_ConvertGui::draw_vline( double radius )
9401 {
9402  double r[ 2 ];
9403 
9404  r[ 0 ] = radius;
9405  r[ 1 ] = radius;
9406 #if QT_VERSION > 0x050000
9407  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = (QwtScaleDiv*)&data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft );
9408 #else
9409  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft );
9410 #endif
9411 
9412  double padding = ( y_axis->upperBound() - y_axis->lowerBound() ) / 30.0;
9413 
9414  double v[ 2 ];
9415  v [ 0 ] = y_axis->upperBound() - padding;
9416  v [ 1 ] = y_axis->lowerBound() + padding;
9417 
9418  QwtPlotCurve* v_line = us_curve( data_plot, "V-Line" );
9419  v_line->setSamples( r, v, 2 );
9420 
9421  QPen pen = QPen( QBrush( Qt::white ), 2.0 );
9422  v_line->setPen( pen );
9423 
9424  data_plot->replot();
9425 }

9664 // Reset with lambda delta,range changes
9665 void US_ConvertGui::reset_lambdas()
9666 {
9667  if ( ! isMwl )
9668  return;
9669 
9670  int plambda = cb_lambplot->currentText().toInt();
9671  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
9672

9674  mwl_data.set_lambdas ( slambda, elambda, tripListx );
9675  mwl_connect( false );
9676 
9677  nlambda = mwl_data.lambdas( exp_lambdas );
9678  int plx = nlambda / 2;
9679  cb_lambplot->clear();
9680 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: nlambda" << nlambda;
9681 
9682  for ( int wvx = 0; wvx < nlambda; wvx++ )
9683  { // Add to plot-lambda list and possibly detect old selection in new list
9684  int ilamb = exp_lambdas[ wvx ];
9685  cb_lambplot->addItem( QString::number( ilamb ) );
9686 
9687  if ( ilamb == plambda ) plx = wvx;
9688  }
9689 
9690 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: plambda" << plambda << "plx" << plx;
9691  cb_lambplot->setCurrentIndex( plx );
9692 
9693  // Rebuild list of triples
9694  QStringList celchns;
9695  QString pwvln = " / " + QString::number( exp_lambdas[ 0 ] )
9696  + "-" + QString::number( exp_lambdas[ nlambda - 1 ] )
9697  + " (" + QString::number( nlambda ) + ")";
9698 
9699  int ncelchn = mwl_data.cellchannels( celchns );
9700  nlambda = mwl_data.countOf( "lambda" );
9701 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: ncc nl szcc szci" << ncelchn << nlambda << celchns.count()
9702  << all_chaninfo.count();
9703 
9704  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncelchn; ii++ )
9705  { // Redo internal channel information description field
9706  all_chaninfo[ ii ].tripleDesc = celchns[ ii ] + pwvln;
9707  }
9708 
9709  mwl_connect( true );
9710  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
9711 
9712  setTripleInfo();
9713 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: sTrInf RTN";
9714 
9715  init_excludes();
9716 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: InExcl RTN";
9717

9719 DbgLv(1) << "rsL: PlCurr RTN";

9724 // Do pseudo-absorbance calculation and apply for MultiWaveLength case
9725 void US_ConvertGui::PseudoCalcAvgMWL( void )
9726 {
9727  for (int ii = 0; ii < outData.size(); ii++ ) {
9728  DbgLv(1) << "PseudoCalcAvgMWL: CCW: " << outData.at(ii)->cell << " / " <<
9729  outData.at(ii)->channel << " / " << outData[ii]->scanData.first().wavelength <<
9730  " : nscans : " << outData[ii]->scanCount();
9731  }
9732  QVector< double > ri_prof; // RI profile for a single wavelength
9733  ExpData.RIProfile.clear(); // Composite RI profile
9734  ExpData.RIwvlns .clear(); // RI profile wavelengths
9735 
9736  if ( referenceDefined ) return; // Average calculation is already done
9737 
9738  US_DataIO::RawData* refData = outData[ tripDatax ];
9739  int ref_size = refData->xvalues.size();
9740  int ccx = tripListx;
9741  int tripx = out_chandatx[ ccx ];
9742  ExpData.RI_nscans = refData->scanData.size();
9743 DbgLv(1) << "PseCalcAvgMWL: ccx tripx nlambda" << ccx << tripx << nlambda;
9744 
9745  QVector<int> unified_lambdas;
9746  QVector<int> unified_lambdas_tripx;
9747  int counter = 0;
9748  QVector<int> argsort;
9749 
9750  for ( int ii = 0; ii < outData.size(); ii++) {
9751  int wvl = qRound( outData.at(ii)->scanData.first().wavelength );
9752  if (unified_lambdas.contains(wvl)) {
9753  continue;
9754  }
9755  unified_lambdas << wvl;
9756  unified_lambdas_tripx << ii;
9757  argsort << counter++;
9758 DbgLv(1) << "PseCalcAvgMWL: added_lambda tripx " << wvl << ii;
9759  }
9760  ExpData.RI_nwvlns = unified_lambdas.size();
9761 DbgLv(1) << "PseCalcAvgMWL: tripx nlambda_i nlambda_f" << tripx << nlambda << unified_lambdas.size();
9762 
9763  std::sort( argsort.begin(), argsort.end(), [&unified_lambdas] (int a, int b) {
9764  return unified_lambdas.at(a) < unified_lambdas.at(b); } );
9765  // Loop to calculate reference data for each wavelength,
9766  // then apply it to all triples with that same wavelength.
9767  for ( int ii = 0; ii < argsort.size(); ii++)
9768  {
9769  int iwavl = unified_lambdas.at(argsort.at(ii));
9770  tripx = unified_lambdas_tripx.at(argsort.at(ii));
9771  refData = outData[ tripx ];
9772  ri_prof.clear();
9773 
9774  // Get the reference profile for the current wavelength
9775  for ( int ss = 0; ss < ExpData.RI_nscans; ss++ )
9776  {
9777  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &refData->scanData[ ss ];
9778 
9779  int rr = 0;
9780  int count = 0;
9781  double sum = 0.0;
9782 
9783  while ( refData->radius( rr ) < reference_start && rr < ref_size )
9784  rr++;
9785 
9786  while ( refData->radius( rr ) < reference_end &&
9787  rr < ref_size )
9788  {
9789  sum += scan->rvalues[ rr ];
9790  count++;
9791  rr++;
9792  }
9793 
9794 
9795  //ALEXEY: check for non-positive data (sum):
9796  double rip_avg;
9797  //double rip_avg = count > 0 ? ( sum / (double)count ) : 1.0;
9798  if ( count > 0 )
9799  {
9800  if ( sum > 0 )
9801  rip_avg = sum / (double)count;
9802  else
9803  rip_avg = 1.0;
9804  }
9805  else
9806  rip_avg = 1.0;
9807 
9808  ri_prof << rip_avg;
9809  ExpData.RIProfile << rip_avg;
9810 
9811  } // END: scan loop for reference triple
9812 
9813  int rip_size = ri_prof.size();
9814 // int iwavl = exp_lambdas[ wvx ];
9815 DbgLv(1) << "PseCalcAvgMWL: wvx" << tripx << "rsiz wavl" << rip_size << iwavl;
9816  ExpData.RIwvlns << iwavl;
9817 
9818  // Now calculate the pseudo-absorbance for all cell/channel/this-lambda
9819  for ( int trx = 0; trx < outData.size(); trx++ )
9820  {
9821  int jwavl = out_triples[ trx ].section( " / ", -1, -1 ).toInt();
9822 
9823  if ( jwavl != iwavl ) continue;
9824 
9825  // Triple data has the current wavelength value
9826  US_DataIO::RawData* currentData = outData[ trx ];
9827 
9828  for ( int ss = 0; ss < currentData->scanData.size(); ss++ )
9829  {
9830  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &currentData->scanData[ ss ];
9831  // Check for boundary condition
9832  int ndx = ( ss < rip_size ) ? ss : rip_size - 1;
9833  double ripval = ri_prof[ ndx ];
9834 
9835  for ( int rr = 0; rr < scan->rvalues.size(); rr++ )
9836  {
9837  // Protect against possible inf's and nan's, if a reading
9838  // evaluates to 0 or wherever log function is undefined or -inf
9839  double rvalue = qMax( 1.0, scan->rvalues[ rr ] );
9840 
9841  scan->rvalues[ rr ] = log10( ripval / rvalue );
9842  } // END: readings loop for a scan
9843 
9844  } // END: scan loop for a specific triple
9845 
9846  } // END: cell-channel apply loop for one wavelength
9847 
9848 // tripx++;
9849 //DbgLv(1) << "PseCalcAvgMWL: tripx" << tripx;
9850  } // END: WaveLength loop
9851 
9852  isPseudo = true;
9853  referenceDefined = true;
9854 DbgLv(1) << "CGui: (9)referDef=" << referenceDefined;
9855  pb_intensity->setEnabled( true );
9856  pb_reference->setEnabled( false );
9857  pb_cancelref->setEnabled( true );
9858 }

9889  }
9890

9892

9910  {
9911  break;
9912  }

9914  elambdas_per_channel[ccx] = exp_lambdas[ nlambda_per_channel - 1 ];
9915  }
9916  /****************************************************************************************************/
9917 DbgLv(1) << "MwlSet: slams_ch:" << slambdas_per_channel;
9918 DbgLv(1) << "MwlSet: elams_ch:" << elambdas_per_channel;
9919 
9920 
9921  show_mwl_control( true );
9922  mwl_connect( true );
9923

9925  le_description -> setText( allData[ 0 ].description );
9926

9928  init_excludes();
9929 
9930  plot_current();
9931 
9932  saveStatus = NOT_SAVED;
9933 
9934  // Ok to enable some buttons now
9935  enableControls();
9936 
9937  int rlamb_s = all_lambdas[ 0 ];
9938  int rlamb_e = all_lambdas[ nlamb_i - 1 ];
9939  int ntriple = all_tripinfo.size();
9940  static QChar clambda( 955 ); // Lambda character
9941  QString lambmsg = tr( "MWL imported : %1 triples : %2 %3 to %4" )
9942  .arg( ntriple ).arg( clambda ).arg( rlamb_s ).arg( rlamb_e );
9943 // le_lambraw->setText( lambmsg );
9944  le_status->setText( lambmsg );
9945  qApp->processEvents();
9946  adjustSize();
9947 }

9949 // Initialize output data pointers and lists
9950 bool US_ConvertGui::init_output_data()
9951 {
9952  bool success = true;
9953  bool have_trip = ( all_tripinfo.size() == allData.size() );
9954 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: have_trip" << have_trip;
9955  if ( ! have_trip )
9956  all_tripinfo.clear();
9957  outData .clear();
9958  all_chaninfo.clear();
9959  all_triples .clear();
9960  all_channels.clear();
9961  out_tripinfo.clear();
9962  out_chaninfo.clear();
9963  out_triples .clear();
9964  out_channels.clear();
9965  out_chandatx.clear();
9966 
9967  // Set up initial export-data pointers list and all/out lists
9968  for ( int trx = 0; trx < allData.size(); trx++ )
9969  {
9970  US_DataIO::RawData* edata = &allData[ trx ];
9971  US_Convert::TripleInfo tripinfo;
9972  US_Convert::TripleInfo chaninfo;
9973 
9974  outData << edata;
9975 
9976  if ( have_trip )
9977  tripinfo = all_tripinfo[ trx ];
9978 
9979  QString triple = QString::number( edata->cell ) + " / "
9980  + QString( edata->channel ) + " / "
9981  + ( ! runType.contains( "W" )
9982  ? QString::number( qRound( edata->scanData[ 0 ].wavelength ) )
9983  : tripinfo.tripleDesc.section( " / ", 2, 2 ) );
9984  QString celchn = triple.section( " / ", 0, 1 );
9985  int chanID = all_channels.indexOf( celchn ) + 1;
9986  chanID = ( chanID < 1 ) ? ( all_channels.count() + 1 ) : chanID;
9987  tripinfo.tripleID = trx + 1;
9988  tripinfo.tripleDesc = triple;
9989  tripinfo.description = edata->description;
9990  tripinfo.channelID = chanID;
9991  tripinfo.excluded = false;
9992  chaninfo = tripinfo;
9993  chaninfo.tripleDesc = celchn;
9994 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: trx" << trx << "triple" << triple;
9995 
9996  if ( have_trip )
9997  all_tripinfo[ trx ] = tripinfo;
9998  else
9999  all_tripinfo << tripinfo;
10000  out_tripinfo << tripinfo;
10001  all_triples << triple;
10002  out_triples << triple;
10003 
10004  if ( ! all_channels.contains( celchn ) || runType.contains( "W" ) )
10005  {
10006  all_channels << celchn;
10007  all_chaninfo << chaninfo;
10008  out_channels << celchn;
10009  out_chaninfo << chaninfo;
10010  out_chandatx << trx;
10011 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: ochx" << trx << "celchn cID" << celchn << chanID;
10012  }
10013  }
10014 
10015  // Save a vector of speed steps read or computed from the data scans
10016  char chtype[ 3 ] = { 'R', 'A', '\0' };
10017  strncpy( chtype, allData[ 0 ].type, 2 );
10018  QString dataType = QString( chtype ).left( 2 );
10019  int nspeed = US_SimulationParameters::readSpeedSteps( runID, dataType,
10020  speedsteps );
10021  int nspeedc = 0;
10022  bool low_accel = false;
10023  double rate = 400.0;
10024 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: rSS nspeed" << nspeed;
10025 
10026  if ( nspeed == 0 )
10027  { // Compute speed steps from all raw auc data
10028  US_SimulationParameters::computeSpeedSteps( allData, speedsteps );
10029  nspeedc = speedsteps.size();
10030  nspeed = nspeedc;
10031 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: cSS nspeed" << speedsteps.size();
10032 
10033  // Check to see if implied 1st acceleration is too low
10034 #define DSS_LO_ACC 250.0 // default SetSpeedLowAccel
10035  if ( impType != 2 ) // Check if not imported AUC
10036  {
10037  QString dbgval = US_Settings::debug_value( "SetSpeedLowAcc" );
10038  double ss_lo_acc = dbgval.isEmpty() ? DSS_LO_ACC : dbgval.toDouble();
10039  low_accel = US_AstfemMath::low_acceleration( speedsteps, ss_lo_acc, rate );
10040  }
10041  }
10042 
10043  // Report problematic 1st speed step
10044  if ( low_accel )
10045  {
10046  int tf_scan = speedsteps[ 0 ].time_first;
10047  int accel1 = (int)qRound( rate );
10048  int rspeed = speedsteps[ 0 ].rotorspeed;
10049  double tf_aend = static_cast<double>(tf_scan);
10050  // prevent any division by zero
10051  if (accel1 != 0)
10052  {
10053  tf_aend = static_cast<double>(rspeed) / static_cast<double>(accel1);
10054  }
10055 
10056 
10057  QString wmsg = tr( "The SpeedStep computed/used is likely bad:<br/>"
10058  "The acceleration implied is %1 rpm/sec.<br/>"
10059  "The acceleration zone ends at %2 seconds,<br/>"
10060  "with a first scan time of %3 seconds.<br/><br/>"
10061  "<b>You should rerun the experiment without<br/>"
10062  "any interim constant speed, and then<br/>"
10063  "you should reimport the data.</b>" )
10064  .arg( accel1 ).arg( QString::number(tf_aend) ).arg( QString::number(tf_scan) );
10065 
10066  QMessageBox msgBox( this );
10067  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Bad TimeState Implied!" ) );
10068  msgBox.setTextFormat( Qt::RichText );
10069  msgBox.setText( wmsg );
10070  msgBox.addButton( tr( "Continue" ), QMessageBox::RejectRole );
10071  QPushButton* bAbort = msgBox.addButton( tr( "Abort" ),
10072  QMessageBox::YesRole );
10073  msgBox.setDefaultButton( bAbort );
10074  msgBox.exec();
10075  if ( msgBox.clickedButton() == bAbort )
10076  { // Abort the import of this data
10077  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
10078  qApp->processEvents();
10079  reset();
10080  return false;
10081  }
10082  else
10083  { // Modify times and omegas of this data, then proceed to import
10084  int status = US_Convert::adjustSpeedstep( allData, speedsteps );
10085 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: adjSS stat" << status;
10086  }
10087  }
10088 
10089  // MultiWaveLength if channels and triples counts differ
10090  isMwl = ( all_chaninfo.count() != all_tripinfo.count() );
10091  if ( isMwl && ( all_tripinfo.count() / all_chaninfo.count() ) < 4 )
10092  { // If less than 4 wavelengths, treat as non-MWL
10093  isMwl = false;
10094  all_chaninfo = all_tripinfo;
10095  out_chaninfo = out_tripinfo;
10096  out_chandatx.clear();
10097 
10098  for ( int jj = 0; jj < out_tripinfo.count(); jj++ )
10099  out_chandatx << jj;
10100 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: isMwl" << isMwl << "ac.count at.count oc.count"
10101  << all_chaninfo.count() << all_tripinfo.count() << out_chaninfo.count();
10102  }
10103 
10104  if ( isMwl )
10105  { // If MWL, update speed steps
10106 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: updSS call";
10107  QVector< SP_SPEEDPROFILE > testss = speedsteps;
10108  int nstest = mwl_data.update_speedsteps( testss );
10109  if ( nstest > 0 )
10110  {
10111  nspeed = nstest;
10112  speedsteps = testss;
10113  }
10114  else if ( nstest < 0 )
10115  {
10116  QMessageBox::critical( this,
10117  tr( "Invalid MWL Speedsteps" ),
10118  tr( "The \"set_speed\" values in MWRS files have"
10119  " resulted in too many speed steps or steps"
10120  " where speeds decrease.\n\nImport is ABORTED!!" ) );
10121  success = false;
10122  resetAll();
10123  }
10124 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: updSS nspeed nstest nspeedc"
10125  << nspeed << nstest << nspeedc << "ss0 timf omgf"
10126  << speedsteps[0].time_first << speedsteps[0].w2t_first;
10127  }
10128 
10129  else
10130  { // Else complete channel lists
10131  for ( int trx = 0; trx < all_tripinfo.count(); trx++ )
10132  {
10133  QString triple = all_tripinfo[ trx ].tripleDesc;
10134 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: trx" << trx << "triple" << triple;
10135  all_chaninfo[ trx ].tripleDesc = triple;
10136  out_chaninfo[ trx ].tripleDesc = triple;
10137  }
10138 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: nspeed" << nspeed << "sp0.rspeed sp0.avspeed"
10139  << nspeed << speedsteps[0].rotorspeed << speedsteps[0].avg_speed;
10140  }
10141 
10142 DbgLv(1) << "CGui:IOD: RETURN";
10143  return success;
10144 }
10145 
10146 // Build output data pointers and lists after new exclusions
10147 void US_ConvertGui::build_output_data()
10148 {
10149  DbgLv(1) << "CGui: BOD: allsz" << allData.size() << "outsz" << outData.size();
10150  QVector< US_DataIO::RawData* > tempData = outData;
10151  QList< US_Convert::TripleInfo > temp_tripinfo = out_tripinfo;
10152  QStringList temp_triples = out_triples;
10153  QList< US_Convert::TripleInfo > temp_chaninfo = out_chaninfo;
10154  QStringList temp_channels = out_channels;
10155  QList< int > temp_chandatx = out_chandatx;
10156  outData.clear(); // Pointers to output data
10157  out_tripinfo.clear(); // Output triple information objects
10158  out_triples.clear(); // Output triple strings ("1 / A / 250")
10159  out_chaninfo.clear(); // Output channel information objects
10160  out_channels.clear(); // Output channel strings ("2 / B")
10161  out_chandatx.clear(); // Triple start indexes for each channel
10162  int outx = 0; // Output triple data index
10163 
10164  // Set up updated export-data pointers list and supporting output lists
10165  for (int trx = 0; trx < allData.size(); trx++) {
10166  US_Convert::TripleInfo *tripinfo = &all_tripinfo[trx];
10167 
10168  if (tripinfo->excluded) {
10169  DbgLv(1) << "CGui: BOD: trx" << trx << "EXCLUDED";
10170  continue;
10171  }
10172  bool used_temp = false;
10173  US_Convert::TripleInfo *ttripinfo;
10174  int ttrx;
10175  // check if the non-updated output data pointers and lists already contain the triple
10176  for (int tttrx = 0; tttrx < tempData.size();tttrx++){
10177  US_Convert::TripleInfo *tttripinfo = &temp_tripinfo[tttrx];
10178  if (tttripinfo->tripleID==tripinfo->tripleID) {
10179  // update export-data pointers and lists using the old export-data pointers and lists
10180  DbgLv(1) << "CGui: BOD: trx" << trx << " found in tempData as ttrx " << tttrx;
10181  used_temp = true;
10182  ttripinfo = tttripinfo;
10183  ttrx = tttrx;
10184  break;
10185  }
10186  }
10187  QString triple;
10188  QString celchn;
10189  // update export-data pointers and lists using the raw data
10190  if (!used_temp){
10191  outData << &allData[trx];
10192 
10193  triple = tripinfo->tripleDesc;
10194  celchn = triple.section(" / ", 0, 1);
10195 
10196  out_tripinfo << *tripinfo;
10197  out_triples << triple;
10198  }
10199  else {
10200  outData << tempData[ttrx];
10201 
10202  triple = ttripinfo->tripleDesc;
10203  celchn = triple.section(" / ", 0, 1);
10204 
10205  out_tripinfo << *ttripinfo;
10206  out_triples << triple;
10207  }
10208 
10209  if (!isMwl || !out_channels.contains(celchn)) {
10210  out_channels << celchn;
10211  out_chaninfo << *tripinfo;
10212  out_chandatx << outx;
10213  }
10214  DbgLv(1) << "CGui: BOD: trx" << trx << "add to out" << outx << triple;
10215 
10216  outx++;
10217  }
10218  DbgLv(1) << "CGui: BOD: outsz" << outData.size();
10219 }

10236 // Function to count speeds present in all data
10237 int US_ConvertGui::countSpeeds( QVector< int >& speeds, int* pNotrips )
10238 {
10239  speeds.clear(); // Initial list of unique speeds
10240  int nspeed = 0; // Total unique speeds encountered
10241  int notrips = 0; // Count of total output triples
10242  int nitrips = allData.size(); // Count of input triples
10243  int pspeed = 0; // Speed at previous scan
10244 
10245  if ( isMwl )
10246  { // Skip the speed counting for MWL
10247  return nspeed;
10248  }
10249 
10250  for ( int trx = 0; trx < nitrips; trx++ )
10251  { // Examine the speeds within each triple
10252  US_DataIO::RawData* edata = &allData[ trx ];
10253 
10254  for ( int ss = 0; ss < edata->scanData.size(); ss++ )
10255  { // Test each scan's speed
10256  int speed = qRound( edata->scanData[ ss ].rpm );
10257 
10258  if ( ! speeds.contains( speed ) )
10259  { // New speed: add to list and bump unique-speed count
10260  speeds << speed; // Newly encountered speed
10261  nspeed++; // Count of unique speeds
10262  }
10263 
10264  if ( speed != pspeed )
10265  { // Not the same speed as previous scan: bump out-triple count
10266  pspeed = speed; // Previous speed for next iteration
10267  notrips++; // Count of output triples
10268  }
10269  }
10270 DbgLv(1) << "cS: trx nspeed notrips" << nspeed << notrips;
10271  }
10272 
10273  if ( pNotrips != NULL )
10274  *pNotrips = notrips; // Return number of output triples
10275 
10276  return nspeed; // Return number of unique speeds
10277 DbgLv(1) << "No of speeds from US_CONVERT=" << nspeed;
10278 }
10279 //------------------------------------------------
10280 // Function to write TimeState files to local disk
10281 //------------------------------------------------
10282 int US_ConvertGui::writeTimeStateDisk()
10283 {
10284  US_TimeState timestate;
10285  QString tmst_fbase = runID + ".time_state.tmst";
10286  QString defs_fbase = runID + ".time_state.xml";
10287  QDir writeDir( US_Settings::resultDir() ); // Writes timestate to results directory
10288  QString dirname = writeDir.absolutePath() + "/" + runID + "/";
10289 
10290  //QString tmst_fdir = currentDir;
10291  QString tmst_fdir = dirname;
10292 
10293 
10294  if ( tmst_fdir.right( 1 ) != "/" ) tmst_fdir + "/";
10295  QString tmst_fname = tmst_fdir + tmst_fbase;
10296  QString defs_fname = tmst_fdir + defs_fbase;
10297  QString defs_fnamei = QString( tmst_fnamei ).section( ".", 0, -2 ) + ".xml";
10298  int nspeed = speedsteps.size();
10299  QVector< double > rrpms;
10300  int nmscans = isMwl ? mwl_data.raw_speeds( rrpms ) : 0;
10301 
10302 // QDir writeDir( US_Settings::resultDir() );
10303 // QString dirname = writeDir.absolutePath() + "/" + runID + "/";
10304 
10305 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: runid=" << runID << " Current directory=" << currentDir
10306  << "Time state file name=" << tmst_fname
10307  << "tmst_fnamei" << tmst_fnamei << "nspeed" << nspeed;
10308 
10309  // Determine if TimeState of right character already exists
10310  if ( ! tmst_fnamei.isEmpty() )
10311  { // An input TMST exists
10312  timestate.open_read_data( tmst_fnamei );
10313  bool constti;
10314  double timeinc;
10315  double ftime;
10316  QStringList fkeys;
10317  QStringList ffmts;
10318  int ntimes = timestate.time_range( &constti, &timeinc, &ftime );
10319  int nvalues = timestate.field_keys( &fkeys, &ffmts );
10320  timestate.close_read_data();
10321 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: TMST file exists:" << tmst_fnamei;
10322 
10323  if ( tmst_fnamei == tmst_fname && defs_fnamei == defs_fname )
10324  { // Same paths, so we are done
10325 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: existing TMST in run directory - NO UPDATE.";
10326  //return ntimes;
10327  }
10328 
10329  // See if all file characteristics match what is now needed
10330  bool use_exstsf = ( ntimes >= nmscans ); // Use existing TMST file?
10331  use_exstsf = ( fkeys.contains( "RawSpeed" ) ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10332  use_exstsf = ( nvalues > 2 ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10333  if ( constti )
10334  { // Constant time increment
10335  use_exstsf = ( ntimes > nmscans ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10336  use_exstsf = ( timeinc > 0.0 ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10337  }
10338  else
10339  { // Non-constant time increment
10340  use_exstsf = ( ntimes >= nmscans ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10341  use_exstsf = ( timeinc == 0.0 ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10342  use_exstsf = ( fkeys.contains( "Time" ) ) ? use_exstsf : false;
10343  }
10344 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: use_exstsf" << use_exstsf << "ntimes nmscans nvalues"
10345  << ntimes << nmscans << nvalues;
10346 
10347  if ( use_exstsf )
10348  { // Existing files have enough: we can use them; need to copy?
10349 
10350  if ( tmst_fnamei.contains( "imports" ) )
10351  { // Existing are in */imports, so copy to current (results/run)
10352  QFile::copy( tmst_fnamei, tmst_fname );
10353  QFile::copy( defs_fnamei, defs_fname );
10354 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: COPY from IMPORTS";
10355  }
10356 
10357  else if ( tmst_fnamei.startsWith( tmst_fdir ) )
10358  { // In current directory, so only a name change (move)
10359  if ( tmst_fname != tmst_fnamei )
10360  QFile::rename( tmst_fnamei, tmst_fname );
10361  if ( defs_fname != defs_fnamei )
10362  QFile::rename( defs_fnamei, defs_fname );
10363 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: RENAME in RESULTS";
10364  }
10365 
10366  else
10367  { // They are somewhere else, so copy to current
10368  QFile::copy( tmst_fnamei, tmst_fname );
10369  QFile::copy( defs_fnamei, defs_fname );
10370 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: COPY from OTHER:" << tmst_fnamei;
10371  }
10372 
10373  // Flag destination file as the input file (in case we re-enter)
10374  tmst_fnamei = tmst_fname;
10375  return ntimes;
10376  }
10377 
10378  else if ( tmst_fnamei.startsWith( tmst_fdir ) )
10379  { // Set is in current directory but not useable as is, so delete
10380  QFile::remove( tmst_fnamei );
10381  QFile::remove( defs_fnamei );
10382  tmst_fnamei.clear();
10383 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: DELETE from RESULTS";
10384  }
10385  }
10386 else
10387 DbgLv(1) << "wTS: EMPTY: tmst_fnamei";
10388 
10389  US_DataIO::RawData* rdata = outData[ 0 ];
10390 
10391  simparams.speed_step = speedsteps;
10392 
10393  simparams.sim = ( rdata->channel == 'S' );
10394  int n_times = US_AstfemMath::writetimestate( tmst_fname, simparams, *rdata );
10395 
10396 DbgLv(1) << "number of times in file" << n_times;
10397  // Flag destination file as the input file (in case we re-enter)
10398  QFile::copy( tmst_fnamei, tmst_fname );
10399  tmst_fnamei = tmst_fname;
10400  return n_times;
10401 }

10403 // Function to write TimeState files to the database
10404 int US_ConvertGui::writeTimeStateDB()
10405 {
10406  int status = 0;
10407  US_Passwd pw;
10408  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
10409 
10410  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
10411  {
10412 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: connect" << db.lastErrno() << db.lastError();
10413  return -99;
10414  }
10415 //DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: connect" << db.lastErrno() << db.lastError();
10416 
10417  QDir writeDir( US_Settings::resultDir() ); // Writes timestate to results directory
10418  QString dirname = writeDir.absolutePath() + "/" + runID + "/";
10419 
10420  QString tmst_fdir = dirname;
10421  QString tmst_fbase = runID + ".time_state.tmst";
10422  QString tmst_fname = tmst_fdir + tmst_fbase;
10423  QString tmst_cksm = US_Util::md5sum_file( tmst_fname );
10424 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: fname " << tmst_fname << "cksm" << tmst_cksm<< "fbase" << tmst_fbase;
10425 
10426  // Create a new TimeState DB record, if need be. If one already exists,
10427  // it may be updated or it may be deleted and recreated.
10428  int timestateID = US_TimeState::dbCreate( &db, ExpData.expID, tmst_fname );
10429 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: post-create timestateID" << timestateID;
10430 
10431  // If a TimeState DB record now exists, check for binary data in it.
10432  // If need be, upload binary TMST data
10433  if ( timestateID > 0 )
10434  { // A record has been created/updated/affirmed, so check for data blob
10435  QString cksum;
10436  status = US_TimeState::dbExamine( &db, &timestateID, NULL,
10437  NULL, NULL, &cksum, NULL );
10438 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: examine status" << status << "cksum-db" << cksum;
10439 
10440  if ( status == US_DB2::OK && cksum != tmst_cksm )
10441  { // No or mismatched blob in DB, so upload it
10442  status = US_TimeState::dbUpload( &db, timestateID,
10443  tmst_fname );
10444 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: upload status" << status;
10445  }
10446  }
10447 DbgLv(1) << "wTSdb: Timestate from DB is used";
10448  return status;
10449 }
10450 
10451 // Build lambda controls
10452 void US_ConvertGui::build_lambda_ctrl()
10453 {
10454  if ( ! isMwl )
10455  return;
10456 
10457  // For MWL, rebuild wavelength controls
10458  int ntrip = out_tripinfo.count();
10459 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: ntrip" << ntrip;
10460  int ccx = out_tripinfo[ 0 ].channelID - 1;
10461 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: st ccx" << ccx;
10462  int wvx = 0;
10463  int ccxo = 0;
10464  exp_lambdas.clear();
10465 
10466  for ( int trx = 0; trx < ntrip; trx++ )
10467  { // Loop to add non-excluded wavelengths
10468  int ichan = out_tripinfo[ trx ].channelID - 1;
10469  int iwavl = out_triples [ trx ].section( " / ", 2, 2 ).toInt();
10470 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: trx ichan ccx iwavl" << trx << ichan << ccx << iwavl;
10471 
10472  if ( ichan != ccx )
10473  { // If a new channel, store the previous channel's lambda list
10474  mwl_data.set_lambdas( exp_lambdas, ccxo );
10475 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: trx ichan ccx ccxo iwavl nlam" << trx << ichan << ccx
10476  << ccxo << iwavl << exp_lambdas.count() << wvx;
10477  wvx = 0;
10478  exp_lambdas.clear();
10479 
10480  ccx = ichan;
10481  ccxo++;
10482  }
10483 
10484  exp_lambdas << iwavl;
10485  wvx++;
10486  }
10487 
10488  // Store the last channel's lambdas
10489  mwl_data.set_lambdas( exp_lambdas, ccxo );
10490 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: ccxo nlam" << ccxo << exp_lambdas.count();
10491  mwl_connect( false );
10492 
10493  // Set controls for the currently selected cell/channel in the list
10494  tripListx = lw_triple->currentRow();
10495  nlambda = mwl_data.lambdas( exp_lambdas, tripListx );
10496  slambda = exp_lambdas[ 0 ];
10497  elambda = exp_lambdas[ nlambda - 1 ];
10498 
10499 DbgLv(1) << "BldLCtr: ccx nlam" << 0 << exp_lambdas.count();
10500  cb_lambstrt->setCurrentIndex( all_lambdas.indexOf( slambda ) );
10501  cb_lambstop->setCurrentIndex( all_lambdas.indexOf( elambda ) );
10502  cb_lambplot->setCurrentIndex( nlambda / 2 );
10503  mwl_connect( true );
10504 
10505  reset_lambdas(); // Make sure internal MWL lambdas are right
10506 
10507 }
